INSERT INTO `pages` (`pageid`, `book_id`, `content_arabic`, `content_english`, `page_number`) VALUES
(101, 2, 'هذا اعِتقَادُ الشَّافعـيِّ ومالِـكٍ ** وأبي حنيفةَ ثُـمَّ أحمـدَ يُنْقَـلُ', ' This is the creed of al-Shaafi''ee and Maalik - And Abu Haneefah and then Ahmad which has been transmitted.', 15),
(102, 2, 'وَلِكُلِ حيِّ عاقـلٍ فـي قبـرِهِ ** عملٌ يُقارنُهُ هنـاك ويُسـألُ', ' And every mentally-sound living person will have in his grave - His deeds to accompany him and for which he will be questioned.', 14),
(100, 2, 'فإنْ اتَّبعْتَ سَبِيلَهُـم فَمُوَفَـقٌ ** وإن ابتدعت فما عليك مُعـوِّلُ', ' So if you follow their path, then success have you been granted - And if you innovate then no support (whatsoever) do you have.', 16),
(3, 3, 'وَفِي الْحَدِيثِ: ( رَأْسُ الأَمْرِ الإِسْلامِ، وَعَمُودُهُ الصَّلاةُ، وَذِرْوَةُ سَنَامِهِ الْجِهَادُ فِي سَبِيلِ اللهِ). وَاللهُ أَعْلَمُ. وَصَلَّى اللهُ عَلَى مُحَمَّدٍ وَعلى آلٰه وَصَحْبِهِ وَسَلَّمَ.\r\n', 'And in the hadeeth: “The head of the matter is Islaam and its main pillar is the Prayer. And its highest part is Jihaad in the Cause of Allaah.” And Allaah knows best. May Allaah send His peace and blessings on Muhammad ﷺ, his family and his Companions.', 97),
(4, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ لاَ إِكْرَاهَ فِي الدِّينِ قَد تَّبَيَّنَ الرُّشْدُ مِنَ الْغَيِّ فَمَنْ يَكْفُرْ بِالطَّاغُوتِ وَيُؤْمِن بِاللّهِ فَقَدِ اسْتَمْسَكَ بِالْعُرْوَةِ الْوُثْقَىَ لاَ انفِصَامَ لَهَا وَاللّهُ سَمِيعٌ عَلِيمٌ ﴾ [البقرة: 256]. \r\nوَهَذَا هُوَ مَعْنَى لا إلٰه إِلا اللهُ،', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of ) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“There is no compulsion in the Religion. Verily, the right path has become distinct from the wrong path. So whoever disbelieves in the Taaghoot and believes in Allaah, then he has taken hold of the firmest handhold that will never break. And Allaah is the All-Hearer, the All-Knower.” \r\n- [Surah Al-Baqarah: 256]\r\n\r\nThis is what is meant by the statement Laa Ilaaha IllaaAllaah.', 96),
(5, 3, 'وَالطَّوَاغِيتُ كَثِيرُونَ وَرُؤُوسُهُمْ خَمْسَةٌ: إِبْلِيسُ لَعَنَهُ اللهُ، وَمَنْ عُبِدَ وَهُوَ رَاضٍ، وَمَنْ دَعَا النَّاسَ إِلَى عِبَادَةِ نَفْسِهِ، وَمَنْ ادَّعَى شَيْئًا مِنْ عِلْمِ الْغَيْبِ، وَمَنْ حَكَمَ بِغَيْرِ مَا أَنْزَلَ اللهُ؛', 'The Tawaagheet (pl. of Taaghoot) are many, but their heads are five: \r\n\r\n(1) Iblees (the Devil), may Allaah curse him; \r\n(2) whoever is worshipped while being pleased with that; \r\n(3) whoever calls the people to worship himself; \r\n(4) whoever claims to have knowledge of the Unseen, and \r\n(5) whoever rules by other than what Allaah has revealed.\r\n', 95),
(6, 3, 'قَالَ ابْنُ الْقَيِّمِ ـ رَحِمَهُ اللهُ تَعَالَى: \r\nمَعْنَى الطَّاغُوتِ مَا تَجَاوَزَ بِهِ الْعَبْدُ حَدَّهُ مِنْ مَعْبُودٍ أَوْ مَتْبُوعٍ أَوْ مُطَاعٍ.\r\n', 'Ibn Al-Qayyim, may Allaah have mercy on him, said: “The Taaghoot is someone or something for whose sake a worshipper transgresses limits, such as those who are worshipped, followed or obeyed.”', 94),
(7, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ وَلَقَدْ بَعَثْنَا فِي كُلِّ أُمَّةٍ رَّسُولاً أَنِ اعْبُدُواْ اللّهَ وَاجْتَنِبُواْ الطَّاغُوتَ﴾ [النحل: 36]. \r\nوَافْتَرَضَ اللهُ عَلَى جَمِيعِ الْعِبَادِ الْكُفْرَ بِالطَّاغُوتِ وَالإِيمَانَ بِاللهِ.\r\n', 'The proof for this is Allaah`s saying:“And We have indeed sent a messenger to every nation (saying): \r\n\r\n”Worship Allaah (alone) and avoid the false deities (Taaghoot).” \r\n- [Surah An-Nahl: 36]\r\n\r\nAllaah obligated all of His servants to disbelieve in the Taaghoot and believe in Allaah.', 93),
(8, 3, 'وَكُلُّ أُمَّةٍ بَعَثَ اللهُ إِلَيْهِا رَسُولا مِنْ نُوحٍ إِلَى مُحَمَّدٍ ـ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ ـ يَأْمُرُهُمْ بِعِبَادَةِ اللهِ وَحْدَهُ، وَيَنْهَاهُمْ عَنْ عِبَادَةِ الطَّاغُوتِ؛\r\n', 'Every nation that Allaah sent a messenger to, from Nooh up to Muhammad, he (i.e. the messenger) would command them to worship Allaah alone and forbid them from worshipping the Taaghoot.', 92),
(9, 3, 'وأَّولُهُمْ نُوحٌ عَلَيْهِ السَّلامُ، وَآخِرُهُمْ مُحَمَّدٌ ـ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ ـ وَهُوَ خَاتَمُ النَّبِيِّينَ؛ وَالدَّلِيلُ عَلَى أَنَّ أَوَّلَهُمْ نُوحٌ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ إِنَّا أَوْحَيْنَا إِلَيْكَ كَمَا أَوْحَيْنَا إِلَى نُوحٍ وَالنَّبِيِّينَ مِن بَعْدِهِ ﴾ [النساء:163].\r\n', 'The first of them was Nooh and the last of them was Muhammad, who was the Seal of the Prophets. The proof that Nooh was the first of them is Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Verily, We sent the revelation to you (O Muhammad), just as We sent the revelation to Nooh and the prophets after him.” [Surah An-Nisaa: 163]', 91),
(10, 3, 'وَأَرْسَلَ اللهُ جَمِيعَ الرُّسُلِ مُبَشِّرِينَ وَمُنْذِرِينَ؛ وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ رُّسُلاً مُّبَشِّرِينَ وَمُنذِرِينَ لِئَلاَّ يَكُونَ لِلنَّاسِ عَلَى اللّ حُجَّةٌ بَعْدَ الرُّسُلِ﴾ [النساء: 165].', 'Allaah sent all of the messengers, giving good tidings and warning. The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Messengers bearing good news and warning – in order that mankind could have no plea against Allaah after (the coming of) the Messengers.” \r\n- [Surah An- Nisaa: 165]', 90),
(11, 3, 'وَمَنْ كَذَّبَ بِالْبَعْثِ كَفَرَ، وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ زَعَمَ الَّذِينَ كَفَرُوا أَن لَّن يُبْعَثُوا قُلْ بَلَى وَرَبِّي لَتُبْعَثُنَّ ثُمَّ لَتُنَبَّؤُنَّ بِمَا عَمِلْتُمْ وَذَلِكَ عَلَى اللَّهِ يَسِيرٌ ﴾ [التغابن: 7].\r\n', 'Whoever rejects the resurrection, disbelieves. The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“The disbelievers claim they will never be resurrected. Say (O Muhammad): ‘Yes, by my Lord! You will certainly be resurrected then you will be informed of what deeds you did.` And that is easy for Allaah.” \r\n- [Surah At-Taghaabun: 7]', 89),
(12, 3, 'وَبَعْدَ الْبَعْثِ مُحَاسَبُونَ وَمَجْزِيُّونَ بِأَعْمَالِهِمْ، وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ وَلِلَّهِ مَا فِي السَّمَاوَاتِ وَمَا فِي الأَرْضِ لِيَجْزِيَ الَّذِينَ أَسَاؤُوا بِمَا عَمِلُوا وَيَجْزِيَ الَّذِينَ أَحْسَنُوا بِالْحُسْنَى ﴾ [النجم: 31].\r\n', 'After being resurrected, they will be judged and recompensed for their actions. The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“...that He may recompense those who do evil with that which they have done (i.e. Hellfire), and reward those who do good with what is best (i.e. Paradise).” - [Surah An-Najm: 31]', 88),
(13, 3, 'وقَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ وَاللَّهُ أَنبَتَكُم مِّنَ الأَرْضِ نَبَاتاً * ثُمَّ يُعِيدُكُمْ فِيهَا وَيُخْرِجُكُمْ إِخْرَاجاً ﴾ [نوح: 17، 18].\r\n', 'And (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Allaah has brought you forth from the earth. Afterwards, He will return you into it and (then) bring you forth (once again, i.e. resurrection).” \r\n- [Surah Nooh: 17-18]', 87),
(14, 3, 'وَالنَّاسُ إِذَا مَاتُواْ يُبْعَثُونَ؛ وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ مِنْهَا خَلَقْنَاكُمْ وَفِيهَا نُعِيدُكُمْ وَمِنْهَا نُخْرِجُكُمْ تَارَةً أُخْرَى ﴾ [طه: 55].', 'When people die they will be resurrected. The proof for this is Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“From it (the earth) We created you, and to it We shall return you, and from it We shall bring you out once again.” \r\n- [Surah TaHa: 55]\r\n', 86),
(15, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ عَلَى مَوْتِهِ ـ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ ـ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ إِنَّكَ مَيِّتٌ وَإِنَّهُم مَّيِّتُونَ * ثُمَّ إِنَّكُمْ يَوْمَ الْقِيَامَةِ عِندَ رَبِّكُمْ تَخْتَصِمُونَ ﴾ [الزمر: 30، 31].\r\n', 'The proof that he died is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“You will surely die and they too will surely die. Then on the Day of Recompense, you will be disputing before your Lord.” \r\n- [Surah Az-Zumar: 30-31]\r\n', 85),
(16, 3, 'وَكَمَّلَ اللهُ بِهِ الدِّينَ؛ وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ الْيَوْمَ أَكْمَلْتُ لَكُمْ دِينَكُمْ وَأَتْمَمْتُ عَلَيْكُمْ نِعْمَتِي وَرَضِيتُ لَكُمُ الإِسْلاَمَ دِين﴾ [المائدة: 3].\r\n', 'Allaah perfected and completed his Religion through him. The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\nThis day I have completed your Religion for you, and perfected my Favor upon you. And I am pleased with Islaam as a Religion for you.\r\n- [Surah Al-Maa`idah: 3]', 84),
(17, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿ قُلْ يَا أَيُّهَا النَّاسُ إِنِّي رَسُولُ اللّهِ إِلَيْكُمْ جَمِيع﴾ [الأعراف: 158].\r\n', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Say: ‘O people! Verily, I am the Messenger of Allaah sent to all of you.`” \r\n- [Surah Al-A`raaf: 158]\r\n', 83),
(18, 3, 'وَهَذَا دِينُهُ، لا خَيْرَ إِلا دَلَّ الأُمَّةَ عَلَيْهِ، وَلا شَرَّ إِلا حَذَّرَهَا مِنْهُ، وَالْخَيْرُ الَّذِي دَلَّهَا عَلَيْهِ التَّوْحِيدُ، وَجَمِيعُ مَا يُحِبُّهُ اللهُ وَيَرْضَاهُ، وَالشَّرُ الَّذِي حَذَّرَهَا مِنْهُ الشِّرْكُ، وَجَمِيعُ مَا يَكْرَهُ اللهُ وَيَأْبَاهُ. بَعَثَهُ اللهُ إِلَى النَّاسِ كَافَّةً، وَافْتَرَضَ طَاعَتَهُ عَلَى جَمِيعِ الثَّقَلَيْنِ الْجِنِّ وَالإِنْسِ؛\r\n', 'This was his Religion – there was no good except that he directed his ummah towards it, and there was no evil except that he warned them against it. The good that he directed his ummah to was: Tawheed and everything that Allaah loves and is pleased with. The evil that he warned his ummah about was: Shirk and everything that Allaah hates and rejects. Allaah sent him to all of mankind, and He made it an obligation upon everyone from the two species of Jinn and mankind to obey him.', 82),
(19, 3, 'فَلَمَّا اسْتَقَرَّ فِي الْمَدِينَةِ أُمِرَ بِبَقِيَّةِ شَرَائِعِ الإِسْلامِ، مِثلِ:\r\nالزَّكَاةِ، وَالصَّوْمِ، وَالْحَجِّ، وَالأَذَانِ، وَالْجِهَادِ، وَالأَمْرِ بِالْمَعْرُوفِ وَالنَّهْيِ عَنِ الْمُنْكَرِ، وَغَيْرِ ذَلِكَ مِنْ شَرَائِعِ الإِسْلامِ، أَخَذَ عَلَى هَذَا عَشْرَ سِنِينَ، وَتُوُفِّيَ ـ صَلواتُ اللهِ وَسَلامُهُ عَلَيْهِ ـ وَدِينُهُ بَاقٍ.', 'So when he settled in Madeenah, he commanded all of the remaining Laws of Islaam, such as Zakaat, Fasting, Hajj, Adhaan, Jihaad, commanding good and forbidding evil, as well as the other laws of Islaam. He remained doing this for ten years, and then passed away, peace and blessings of Allaah be on him, while his Religion remained.', 81),
(20, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ عَلَى الْهِجْرَةِ مِنَ السُّنَّةِ: قَوْلُهُ ـ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ ـ: \r\n(لا تَنْقَطِعُ الْهِجْرَةُ حَتَّى تَنْقَطِعَ التَّوْبَةُ، وَلا تَنْقَطِعُ التَّوْبَةُ حَتَّى تَطْلُعَ الشَّمْسُ مِنْ مَغْرِبِهَا).\r\n', 'The proof for Hijrah from the Sunnah is his saying: \r\n\r\n“Hijrah will not cease until repentance ceases. And repentance will not cease (to be accepted) until the sun rises from where it sets (i.e. the west).”', 80),
(21, 3, 'قَالَ الْبُغَوِيُّ ـ رَحِمَهُ اللهُ ـ\r\n:نزلت هَذِهِ الآيَةِ فِي المُسْلِمِينَ الَّذِينَ بِمَكَّةَ ولَمْ يُهَاجِرُوا، نَادَاهُمُ اللهُ بِاسْمِ الإِيمَانِ.\r\n', 'Al-Baghawee, may Allaah have mercy on him, said: \r\n\r\n“The reason for the revelation of this ayah was due to some Muslims who had resided in Makkah and did not migrate (to Madeenah). Allaah called out to them using the title of Eemaan (for them).”', 79),
(22, 3, 'وَقَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ يَا عِبَادِيَ الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا إِنَّ أَرْضِي وَاسِعَةٌ فَإِيَّايَ فَاعْبُدُونِ ﴾ [العنكبوت: 56].\r\n', 'And (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:“O My servants who believe (in Me)! Verily, My earth is spacious so to Me alone, perform your worship. \r\n- [Surah Al-‘Ankaboot: 56]”', 78),
(23, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ إِنَّ الَّذِينَ تَوَفَّاهُمُ الْمَلآئِكَةُ ظَالِمِي أَنْفُسِهِمْ قَالُواْ فِيمَ كُنتُمْ قَالُواْ كُنَّا مُسْتَضْعَفِينَ فِي الأَرْضِ قَالْوَاْ أَلَمْ تَكُنْ أَرْضُ اللّهِ وَاسِعَةً فَتُهَاجِرُواْ فِيهَا فَأُوْلَـئِكَ مَأْوَاهُمْ جَهَنَّمُ وَسَآءتْ مَصِيراً * إِلاَّ الْمُسْتَضْعَفِينَ مِنَ الرِّجَالِ وَالنِّسَآء وَالْوِلْدَانِ لاَ يَسْتَطِيعُونَ حِيلَةً وَلاَ يَهْتَدُونَ سَبِيلاً * فَأُوْلَـئِكَ عَسَى اللّهُ أَن يَعْفُوَ عَنْهُمْ وَكَانَ اللّهُ عَفُوّاً غَفُوراً ﴾ [النساء: 97ـ99].', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Verily, as for those whom  the angels take (in death) while they are wronging themselves (by not performing Hijrah), they (angels) will say (to them): “In what (condition) were you? ” They will reply: “We were weak and oppressed in the earth.” They (angels) will say: “Was not the earth of Allaah spacious enough for you to migrate therein?” Such men will find their abode in Hell – what an evil destination! Except the weak ones among men, and women and children – who cannot devise a plan, nor are they able to direct their way. These are the ones whom Allaah is (most) likely to forgive, and Allaah is Ever Oft-Pardoning, Most Forgiving.” \r\n- [Surah An-Nisaa: 97-99]', 77),
(24, 3, 'وَالْهِجْرَةُ الانْتِقَالُ مِنْ بَلَدِ الشِّرْكِ إِلَى بَلَدِ الإِسْلامِ. وَالْهِجْرَةُ فَرِيضَةٌ عَلَى هَذِهِ الأُمَّةِ مِنْ بَلَدِ الشِّرْكِ إِلَى بلد الإِسْلامِ، وَهِيَ بَاقِيَةٌ إِلَى أَنْ تَقُومَ السَّاعَةُ،\r\n', 'Hijrah means Moving from a land of Shirk to a land of Islaam. It is obligatory upon this ummah to migrate from a land of Shirk to a land of Islaam, and this is everlasting until the (Final) Hour is established.', 76),
(25, 3, 'أَخَذَ عَلَى هَذَا عَشْرَ سِنِينَ يَدْعُو إِلَى التَّوْحِيدِ، وَبَعْدَ الْعَشْرِ عُرِجَ بِهِ إِلَى السَّمَاءِ، وَفُرِضَتْ عَلَيْهِ الصَّلَواتُ الْخَمْسُ، وَصَلَّى فِي مَكَّةَ ثَلاثَ سِنِينَ، وَبَعْدَهَا أُمِرَ بالْهِجْرَةِ إِلَى الْمَدِينَةِ،', 'He remained doing this for ten years, calling the people to Tawheed. And after ten years, he was ascended up to the heaven, where the five daily prayers were made obligatory on him. So he prayed in Makkah for three years and thereafter, he was ordered to make the Hijrah (migration) to Madeenah.', 75),
(26, 3, 'وَمَعْنَى: ﴿ قُمْ فَأَنذِرْ ﴾ : يُنْذِرُ عَنِ الشِّرْكِ، وَيَدْعُو إِلَى التَّوْحِيدِ. \r\n﴿ وَرَبَّكَ فَكَبِّرْ ﴾ : أَيْ: عَظِّمْهُ بِالتَّوْحِيدِ. \r\n﴿ وَثِيَابَكَ فَطَهِّرْ ﴾ : أَيْ: طَهِّرْ أَعْمَالَكَ عَنِ الشِّرْكِ. \r\n﴿ وَالرُّجْزَ فَاهْجُرْ ﴾ : الرُّجْزَ: الأَصْنَامُ، وَهَجْرُهَا: تَرْكُهَا، وَالْبَرَاءَةُ مِنْهَا وَأَهْلُهَا\r\n', 'The meaning of “Rise and warn” is warn against Shirk and call to Tawheed. \r\n\r\n“And magnify your Lord” means glorify Him by way of Tawheed. \r\n\r\n“And purify your garments” means cleanse your actions from Shirk. \r\n\r\n“And abandon ar-rujz.” “Rujz” means statues, and “Abandon” means leave them and free yourself from them and those who worship them.', 74),
(27, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿يَا أَيُّهَا الْمُدَّثِّرُ * قُمْ فَأَنذِرْ * وَرَبَّكَ فَكَبِّرْ * وَثِيَابَكَ فَطَهِّرْ * وَالرُّجْزَ فَاهْجُرْ * وَلاَ تَمْنُن تَسْتَكْثِرُ * وَلِرَبِّكَ فَاصْبِرْ ﴾ [المدثر: 1-7].\r\n', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“O you wrapped in garments. Rise and warn! And magnify your Lord (Allaah). And purify your garments. And abandon ar-rujz (idols). And do not give away something in order to have more. And be patient for the sake of your Lord.” \r\n- [Surah Al-Muddathir: 1-7]', 73),
(28, 3, 'وَبَلَدُهُ مَكَّةُ، بَعَثَهُ اللهُ بِالنِّذَارَةِ عَنِ الشِّرْكِ، وَبالَدْعُوة إِلَى التَّوْحِيدِ،\r\n\r\n', 'His homeland was Makkah, and he (later) migrated to Madeenah. Allaah sent him to warn against Shirk (polytheism) and to call to Tawheed (pure monotheism).\r\n', 72),
(29, 3, 'وَلَهُ مِنَ الِعُمُرِ ثَلاثٌ وَسِتُّونَ سَنَةً، مِنْهَا أَرْبَعُونَ قَبْلَ النُّبُوَّةِ، وَثَلاثٌ وَعِشْرُون َفى النبوة. \r\nنُبِّئَ ب﴿اقْرَأ﴾ ، \r\nوَأُرْسِلَ ب﴿الْمُدَّثِّرْ﴾\r\n', 'He lived for sixty-three years, forty of which was prior to his prophethood and twenty-three of which he spent as a prophet, messenger. He became a prophet due to (the meaning of Allaah`s saying):\r\n\r\n“Read” \r\n- [Surah ‘Alaq: 1] \r\n\r\nand a messenger due to: \r\n\r\n“O you wrapped in garments.” \r\n- [Surah Al-Muddathir: 1]\r\n', 71),
(30, 3, '...قَالَ: فَمَضَى، فَلَبِثْنَا مَلِيَّا، فَقَالَ: ( يَا عُمَرُ أَتَدْرُونَ مَنِ السَّائِلِ؟ ). قُلْت: اللهُ وَرَسُولُهُ أَعْلَمُ، قَالَ: ( هَذَا جِبْرِيلُ أَتَاكُمْ  يُعَلِّمُكُمْ أَمْرَ دِينِكُم).', '...Then he left and we remained (seated) there for a while.Then he said: ‘O ‘Umar, do you know who the questioner was?` I said: ‘Allaah and His Messenger know best.` He said: ‘That was Jibreel who came to you to teach you your Religion.` ”', 69),
(31, 3, 'الأصل الثالث: \r\nمَعْرِفَةُ نَبِيِّكُمْ مُحَمَّدٍ ـ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ وَهُوَ مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عَبْدِ اللهِ بْنِ عَبْدِ الْمُطَّلِبِ بْنِ هَاشِمٍ، وَهَاشِمٌ مِنْ قُرَيْشٍ، وَقُرَيْشٌ مِنَ الْعَرَبِ، وَالْعَرَبُ مِنْ ذُرِّيَّةِ إِسْمَاعِيلَ بْنِ إِبْرَاهِيمَ الْخَلِيلِ عَلَيْهِ وَعَلَى نَبِيِّنَا أَفْضَلُ الصَّلاةِ وَالسَّلامِ.\r\n', 'The Third Principle:\r\n\r\nKnowledge of your Prophet, Muhammad ﷺ : He is Muhammad, the son of ‘Abdullaah, the son of ‘Abdul-Mutallib bin Haashim. Haashim was from the (the tribe of) Quraysh and Quraysh was from the Arabs. And the Arabs are from the offspring of (Prophet) Isma`eel, son of (Prophet) Ibraaheem. May Allaah send the best of His peace and blessings on him and on our Prophet (Muhammad).', 70),
(32, 3, '...قَالَ: فَأَخْبِرْنِي عَنْ أَمَارَاتِهَا. قَالَ: ( أَنْ تَلِدَ الأَمَةُ رَبَّتَهَا، وَأَنْ تَرَى الْحُفَاةَ الْعُرَاةَ الْعَالَةَ رِعَاءَ الشَّاءِ يَتَطَاوَلُونَ فِي الْبُنْيَانِ )...\r\n', '...He said: ‘So then inform me about its signs.` He said: ‘It will be when the mother gives birth to her (female) master, when the barefooted, barren and lowly shepherds will compete with one another in constructing tall buildings.`...\r\n', 68),
(33, 3, '...قَالَ: أَخْبِرْنِي عَنِ السَّاعَةِ. قَالَ: (مَا الْمَسْؤُولُ عَنْهَا بِأَعْلَمَ مِنَ السَّائِلِ )...\r\n', '...He then said: ‘Now inform me about the (Final) Hour.` He said: ‘The one who is being asked does not have any more knowledge of it than the one who is asking.`...\r\n', 67),
(34, 3, '...قَالَ: أَخْبِرْنِي عَنِ الإِحْسَانِ. قَالَ: ( أَنْ تَعْبُدَ اللهَ كَأَنَّكَ تَرَاهُ، فَإِنْ لَمْ تَكُنْ تَرَاهُ فَإِنَّهُ يَرَاكَ )...\r\n', '...Now inform me about Ihsaan. He said: ‘It is that you worship Allaah as if you see Him, but even though you don`t see Him, He indeed sees you.`...', 66),
(35, 3, '...فَعَجِبْنَا لَهُ يَسْأَلُهُ وَيُصَدِّقُهُ. قَالَ: أَخْبِرْنِي عَنِ الإِيمَانِ. قَالَ:(أَنْ تُؤْمِنَ بِاللهِ، وَمَلائِكَتِهِ، وَكُتُبِهِ، وَرُسُلِهِ، وَالْيَوْمِ الآخِرِ، وَتُؤْمِنَ بِالْقَدَرِ خَيْرِهِ وَشَرِّهِ ). قَالَ: صَدَقْتَ...\r\n', '...So we were amazed that he had asked him and then told him that he was truthful. Then he said: ‘Now inform me about Eemaan.` So he said: ‘It is that you believe in Allaah, His angels, His (revealed) books, His messengers, the Last Day, and that you believe in Al-Qadar , the good of it and the bad of it.` He said: ‘You have spoken truthfully...\r\n', 65),
(36, 3, '...وَقَالَ: يَا مُحَمَّدُ أَخْبِرْنِي عَنِ الإِسْلامِ فَقَالَ: ( أَنْ تَشْهَدَ أَنْ لا إلٰه إِلا اللهُ وَأَنَّ مُحَمَّدًا رَسُولُ اللهِ، وَتُقِيمَ الصَّلاةَ، وَتُؤْتِيَ الزَّكَاةَ، وَتَصُومَ رَمَضَانَ، وَتَحُجَّ الْبَيْتَ إِنْ اسْتَطَعْتَ إِلَيْهِ سَبِيلا ). قَالَ: صَدَقْتَ...\r\n', '...and said: ‘O Muhammad, inform me about Islaam.` So he said: ‘It is that you testify that there is no deity that has the right to be worshipped except Allaah and that Muhammad is the Messenger of Allaah. And that you establish the prayer, give the Zakaat, fast during Ramadaan and perform the Hajj (pilgrimage) to (Allaah`s) House, if you are able to do it.` He said: ‘You have spoken truthfully.`', 64),
(37, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ مِنَ السُّنَّةِ: حَدِيثُ جِبْرِيلَ الْمَشْهُورُ: عَنْ عُمَرَ بنِ الْخَطَّابِ ـ رَضِيَ اللهُ عَنْهُ ـ قَالَ: \r\nبَيْنَمَا نَحْنُ جُلُوسٌ عِنْدَ النَّبِيِّ ـ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ ـ إِذْ طَلَعَ عَلَيْنَا رَجُلٌ، شَدِيدُ بَيَاضِ الثِّيَابِ، شَدِيدُ سَوَادِ الشَّعْرِ، لا يُرَى عَلَيْهِ أَثَرُ السَّفَرِ، وَلا يَعْرِفُهُ مِنَّا أَحَدٌ، فَجَلَسَ إِلَى النَّبِيِّ ـ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ ـ فَأَسْنَدَ رُكْبَتَيْهِ إِلَى رُكْبَتَيْهِ، وَوَضَعَ كَفَّيْهِ عَلَى فَخِذَيْهِ...\r\n', 'The proof from the Sunnah is the famous hadeeth of Jibreel, which is reported from  ‘Umar bin Al-Khattaab who said: \r\n\r\n“One day we were sitting with the Prophet when there appeared to us a man with extremely white garments and extremely black hair. No trace of journeying could be seen on him nor did any amongst us recognize him. Then he sat in front of the Prophet, lining up his knees with his knees and placing his palms upon his thighs..."', 63),
(38, 3, 'وقَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿وَمَا تَكُونُ فِي شَأْنٍ وَمَا تَتْلُو مِنْهُ مِن قُرْآنٍ وَلاَ تَعْمَلُونَ مِنْ عَمَلٍ إِلاَّ كُنَّا عَلَيْكُمْ شُهُوداً إِذْ تُفِيضُونَ فِيهِ﴾ [يونس: 61].', 'And (the meaning of) His saying:\r\n\r\n“There is no deed that you (O Muhammad) do, nor any portion of the Qur`aan that you recite, nor any deed that you (humans) do, except that We are witnesses to it, whilst you are doing it.” \r\n- [Surah Yoonus: 61]\r\n', 62),
(39, 3, 'وقَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿وَتَوَكَّلْ عَلَى الْعَزِيزِ الرَّحِيمِ * الَّذِي يَرَاكَ حِينَ تَقُومُ * وَتَقَلُّبَكَ فِي السَّاجِدِينَ * إِنَّهُ هُوَ السَّمِيعُ الْعَلِيمُ ﴾ [الشعراء: 217 ـ 220].\r\n', 'And (the meaning of) His saying:\r\n\r\n“And put your trust in the All-Mighty, the Most Merciful, who sees you when you stand up (for prayer at night), and (who sees) your movements among those who prostrate themselves (to Him). Verily, He is the All-Hearer, the All-Knower.” \r\n- [Surah Ash-Shu`araa: 217-220]\r\n', 61),
(40, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ إِنَّ اللّـهَ مَعَ الّـَذِينَ اتَّقَواْ وَّالّـَذِينَ هُم مُّحْسِنُونَ ﴾ [النحل: 128].\r\n', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Verily, Allaah is with those who have Taqwaa (dutifulness to Allaah) and those who have Ihsaan.” \r\n- [Surah An-Nahl: 128]', 60),
(41, 3, 'الْمَرْتَبَةُ الثَّالِثَةُ: \r\nالإِحْسَانُ رُكْنٌ وَاحِدٌ. و هو أَنْ تَعْبُدَ اللهَ كَأَنَّكَ تَرَاهُ، فَإِن لَمْ تَكُنْ تَرَاهُ فَإِنَّهُ يَرَاكَ .\r\n', 'The Level of Ihsaan: Ihsaan is one pillar, which means: To worship Allaah as if you see Him, but even if you don`t see Him, He indeed sees you.', 59),
(42, 3, 'ودليل القدر: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿إِنَّا كُلَّ شَيْءٍ خَلَقْنَاهُ بِقَدَرٍ ﴾ [القمر: 49].', 'And the proof for Al-Qadar (Pre-Decree) is Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Verily, We have created all things with Qadar (divine pre-decree ordained for it).” \r\n- [Surah Al-Qamar: 49]', 58),
(43, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ عَلَى هَذِهِ الأَرْكَانِ السِّتَةِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ لَّيْسَ الْبِرَّ أَن تُوَلُّواْ وُجُوهَكُمْ قِبَلَ الْمَشْرِقِ وَالْمَغْرِبِ وَلَـكِنَّ الْبِرَّ مَنْ آمَنَ بِاللّهِ وَالْيَوْمِ الآخِرِ وَالْمَلآئِكَةِ وَالْكِتَابِ وَالنَّبِيِّينَ﴾ [البقرة: 177].\r\n', 'The proof for these six pillars is Allaah`s statement:\r\n\r\n“Righteousness (birr) is not that you turn your faces towards the east and the west (in prayer), but rather righteousness (birr) is (for) the one who believes in Allaah, the Last Day, the Angels, the Books and the Prophets.” \r\n- [Surah Al- Baqarah: 177]', 57),
(44, 3, 'وَأَرْكَانُهُ سِتَّةٌ: \r\nكما فى الحديث (أَنْ تُؤْمِنَ بِاللهِ، وَمَلائِكَتِهِ،  وَكُتُبِهِ، وَرُسُلِهِ، وَالْيَوْمِ الآخِرِ، وَتُؤْمِنَ بِالْقَدَرِ خَيْرِهِ وَشَرِّهِ).\r\n', 'Its pillars are six: \r\n\r\n(1) That you believe in Allaah, \r\n(2) His angels, \r\n(3) His books, \r\n(4) His Messengers, \r\n(5) the Last Day, and \r\n(6) that you believe in Al-Qadar (Divine Pre- Decree) – the good of it and the bad of it.', 56),
(45, 3, 'الْمَرْتَبَةُ الثَّانِيَةُ: \r\nالإِيمَانُ وَهُوَ: بِضْعٌ وَسَبْعُونَ شُعْبَةً، فَأَعْلاهَا قَوْلُ لا إلٰه إِلا اللهُ، وَأَدْنَاهَا إِمَاطَةُ الأَذَى عَنِ الطَّرِيقِ، وَالْحَيَاءُ شُعْبَةٌ مِنْ الإِيمَانِ.\r\n', 'The Level of Eemaan: \r\n\r\nEemaan consists of more than seventy branches. The highest of them is saying Laa Ilaaha IllaaAllaah and the lowest of them is moving a harmful object from the road. And Hayaa (modesty) is a branch from Eemaan.', 55),
(46, 3, 'ودَلِيلُ الْحَجِّ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿وَلِلّهِ عَلَى النَّاسِ حِجُّ الْبَيْتِ مَنِ اسْتَطَاعَ إِلَيْهِ سَبِيلاً وَمَن كَفَرَ فَإِنَّ الله غَنِيٌّ عَنِ الْعَالَمِينَ ﴾ [آل عمران: 97].\r\n', 'The proof for Hajj is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\nAnd the Hajj (pilgrimage) to the House (Ka`bah) is a duty that mankind owes to Allaah for those who are able to do it. And whoever disbelieves (by denying Hajj), then indeed  Allaah is not in need of any of His creation.” \r\n- [Surah Aali ‘Imraan: 97]', 54),
(47, 3, 'ودَلِيلُ الصِّيَامِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿يَا أَيُّهَا الَّذِينَ آمَنُواْ كُتِبَ عَلَيْكُمُ الصِّيَامُ كَمَا كُتِبَ عَلَى الَّذِينَ مِن قَبْلِكُمْ لَعَلَّكُمْ تَتَّقُونَ ﴾ [البقرة: 183].\r\n', 'The proof for Fasting is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“O you who believe! Fasting is prescribed for you just as it was prescribed for those before you, in order that you may acquire Taqwaa (dutifulness to Allaah).” \r\n- [Surah Al-Baqarah: 183]', 53),
(48, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الصَّلاةِ، وَالزَّكَاةِ، وَتَفْسِيرُ التَّوْحِيدِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿وَمَا أُمِرُوا إِلاَّ لِيَعْبُدُوا اللَّهَ مُخْلِصِينَ لَهُ الدِّينَ حُنَفَآءَ وَيُقِيمُوا الصَّلاةَ وَيُؤْتُوا الزَّكَاةَ وَذَلِكَ دِينُ الْقَيِّمَةِ ﴾ [البينة: 5].', 'The proof for Prayer and Zakaat and the explanation of Tawheed is found in (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“And they were not commanded except that they should worship Allaah, making the religion (i.e. worship) solely for Him alone, and that they should perform the prayer and give the Zakaat. And that is the right Religion.” - [Surah Al-Bayyinah: 5]', 52),
(49, 3, 'وَمَعْنَى شَهَادَة أَنَّ مُحَمَّدًا رَسُولُ اللهِ: \r\nطَاعَتُهُ فِيمَا أَمَرَ، وَتَصْدِيقُهُ فِيمَا أَخْبَرَ، واجْتِنَابُ مَا نَهَى عَنْهُ وَزَجَرَ وأَلا يُعْبَدَ اللهُ إِلا بِمَا شَرَعَ.\r\n', 'The meaning of testifying that Muhammad is the Messenger of Allaah is: Obeying him in what he has commanded, believing him in what he has informed us of, avoiding what  he forbade and warned against, and not worshipping Allaah except by what he prescribed.', 51),
(50, 3, 'وَدليلُ شَهَادَةِ أَنَّ مُحَمَّدًا رَسُولُ اللهِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ لَقَدْ جَآءكُمْ رَسُولٌ مِّنْ أَنفُسِكُمْ عَزِيزٌ عَلَيْهِ مَا عَنِتُّمْ حَرِيصٌ عَلَيْكُم بِالْمُؤْمِنِينَ رَؤُوفٌ رَّحِيمٌ ﴾ [التوبة: 128].', 'The proof for testifying that Muhammad is the Messenger of Allaah is (the meaning of) His saying:Verily there has come to you a Messenger from amongst yourselves. It grieves him that you should receive any injury or difficulty. He is anxious over you (to be guided) and he is full of kindness and mercy towards the believers.” \r\n- [Surah At-Tawbah: 128]', 50),
(51, 3, 'وقَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿قُلْ يَا أَهْلَ الْكِتَابِ تَعَالَوْاْ إِلَى كَلَمَةٍ سَوَاءٍ بَيْنَنَا وَبَيْنَكُمْ أَلاَّ نَعْبُدَ إِلاَّ اللّهَ وَلاَ نُشْرِكَ بِهِ شَيْئاً وَلاَ يَتَّخِذَ بَعْضُنَا بَعْضاً أَرْبَاباً مِّن دُونِ اللّهِ فَإِن تَوَلَّوْاْ فَقُولُواْ اشْهَدُواْ بِأَنَّا مُسْلِمُونَ ﴾ [آل عمران: 64].\r\n', 'And (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Say: ‘O People of the Scripture (i.e. Jews and Christians)! Come to a word that is just between us and you – that we worship none but Allaah alone and that we associate no  partners with Him; and that none of us shall take others as lords besides Allaah.` Then if they turn away, say: ‘Bear witness that we are Muslims.`” \r\n- [Surah Aali ‘Imraan: 64]', 49),
(52, 3, 'وَتَفْسِيرُهَا: الَّذِي يُوَضِّحُهَا قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى \r\n﴿وَإِذْ قَالَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ لأَبِيهِ وَقَوْمِهِ إِنَّنِي بَرَآء مِّمَّا تَعْبُدُونَ * إِلاَّ الَّذِي فَطَرَنِي فَإِنَّهُ سَيَهْدِينِ * وَجَعَلَهَا كَلِمَةً بَاقِيَةً فِي عَقِبِهِ لَعَلَّهُمْ يَرْجِعُونَ ﴾ [الزخرف: 26 - 28].\r\n', 'An explanation of this, which will clarify it further, is found in (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“And remember when Ibraaheem said to his father and to his people:  ‘Verily, I am free from all that you worship – except for He who created Me, and verily He will guide me.` And He made it a statement that will endure among his offspring that they may turn back to.” \r\n- [Surah Az-Zukhruf: 26-28]', 48),
(53, 3, '﴿لا إلٰه﴾ نَافِيًا جَمِيعَ مَا يُعْبَدُ مِنْ دُونِ اللهِ ﴿إِلا اللهُ﴾ مُثْبِتًا الْعِبَادَةَ للهِ وَحْدَهُ لا شَرِيكَ لَهُ فِي عِبَادَتِهِ، كَمَا أَنَّهُ لَيْسَ لَهُ شَرِيكٌ فِي مُلْكِهِ.\r\n', 'Laa Ilaaha negates everything that is worshipped besides Allaah, while IllaaAllaah affirms the worship of only Allaah, free from any partner being mixed in with His worship, just as there is no partner mixed in with His Dominion.', 47),
(54, 3, 'وَمَعْنَاهَا: لا مَعْبُودَ بِحَقٍّ إلا اللهُ،\r\n', 'The meaning of it (i.e. the testimony of Faith) is (the meaning of His saying): There is no one that has the right to be worshipped except Allaah, alone.', 46),
(55, 3, 'فَدَلِيلُ الشَّهَادَةِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿ شَهِدَ اللّهُ أَنَّهُ لاَ إلٰه إِلاَّ هُوَ وَالْمَلاَئِكَةُ وَأُوْلُواْ الْعِلْمِ قَآئِمَاً بِالْقِسْطِ لاَ إلٰه إِلاَّ هُوَ الْعَزِيزُ الْحَكِيمُ ﴾ [آل عمران، 18].\r\n', 'The proof for the testimony of Faith is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\nAllaah bears witness that there is no deity that has the right to be worshipped except Him, and so do the angels and those who possess knowledge. He is always maintaining His creation with justice. None has the right to be worshipped but Him – the All-Mighty, the All-Wise.” \r\n- [Surah Aali ‘Imraan: 18]', 45),
(56, 3, 'المرتبة الأولى: الإسلام فَأَرْكَانُ الإِسْلامِ خَمْسَةٌ: شَهَادَةُ أَن لا إلٰه إِلا اللهُ وَأَنَّ مُحَمَّدًا رَسُولُ اللهِ، وَإِقَامُ الصَّلاةِ، وَإِيتَاءِ الزَّكَاةِ، وَصَوْمُ رَمَضَانَ، وَحَجُّ بَيْتِ اللهِ الْحَرَامِ.\r\n', 'The Level of Islaam: The pillars of Islaam are five: \r\n(1) The testimony that there is no deity that has the right to be worshipped except Allaah, and that Muhammad is the Messenger of Allaah; \r\n(2) Establishing the Prayer; \r\n(3) Giving the Zakaat; \r\n(4) Fasting in Ramadaan; \r\n(5) Performing Hajj to Allaah`s Sacred House.', 44),
(57, 3, 'الأصل الثاني: مَعْرِفَةُ دِينِ الإِسْلامِ بِالأَدِلَّةِ وَهُوَ: الاسْتِسْلامُ للهِ بِالتَّوْحِيدِ، وَالانْقِيَادُ لَهُ بِالطَّاعَةِ، وَالْبَرَاءَةُ مِنَ الشِّرْكِ وَأَهْلِهِ، وَهُوَ ثَلاثُ مَرَاتِبَ: الإسْلامُ، وَالإِيمَانُ، وَالإِحْسَانُ. وَكُلُّ مَرْتَبَةٍ لَهَا أَرْكَانٌ.\r\n', 'The Second Fundamental Principle: Knowing the Religion of Islaam, based on evidences. This (i.e. Islaam) means submitting to Allaah by way of Tawheed, surrendering one`s  (full) obedience to Him, and absolving oneself from Shirk and its people. This can be divided into three levels: \r\n1. Islaam \r\n2. Eemaan, and \r\n3. Ihsaan \r\nEach one of these levels has its own pillars.', 43),
(58, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ النَّذْرِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿يُوفُونَ بِالنَّذْرِ وَيَخَافُونَ يَوْماً كَانَ شَرُّهُ مُسْتَطِيراً ﴾ [الإنسان: 7].\r\n', 'The proof for Making Oaths is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“They are those who fulfill their vows and fear a Day whose evil will be widespread.” \r\n- [Surah Al-Insaan: 7]', 42),
(59, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الإِنَابَةِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿وَأَنِيبُوا إِلَى رَبِّكُمْ وَأَسْلِمُوا لَهُ...﴾ الآية [الزمر: 54].\r\n', 'The proof for Repentance is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“And turn to your Lord in repentance and submit to Him [as Muslims].” \r\n- [Surah Az-Zumar: 54]\r\n', 35),
(60, 3, 'وَمِنَ السُنَّةِ: (لعَنَ اللهُ مَنْ ذَبَحَ لِغَيْرِ اللهِ).\r\n', 'And from the Sunnah is:\r\n\r\n“May Allaah curse the one who offers a sacrifice to other than Allaah.”', 41),
(61, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الذَّبْحِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿قُلْ إِنَّنِي هَدَانِي رَبِّي إِلَى صِرَاطٍ مُّسْتَقِيمٍ دِيناً قِيَماً مِّلَّةَ إِبْرَاهِيمَ حَنِيفاً وَمَا كَانَ مِنَ الْمُشْرِكِينَ * قُلْ إِنَّ صَلاَتِي وَنُسُكِي وَمَحْيَايَ وَمَمَاتِي لِلّهِ رَبِّ الْعَالَمِينَ * لاَ شَرِيكَ لَه وَبِذَلِكَ أُمِرْتُ وَأَنَا أَوَّلُ الْمُسْلِمِينَ ُ﴾ [الأنعام: 161-163].', 'The proof for offering sacrifices is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Say: Verily my prayer, my sacrificial offerings, my living and my dying are for Allaah, Lord of the Worlds. He has no partner...” \r\n- [Surah Al-An`aam: 162-163]', 40),
(62, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الاسْتِغَاثَةِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿إِذْ تَسْتَغِيثُونَ رَبَّكُمْ فَاسْتَجَابَ لَكُمْ...﴾ الآية [الأنفال: 9].\r\n', 'The proof for Asking for Help is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“And remember when you sought help from your Lord and He responded to you…” \r\n- [Surah Al-Anfaal: 9]', 39),
(63, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الاسْتِعَاذَةِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿قُلْ أَعُوذُ بِرَبِّ الْفَلَقِ ﴾ [الفلق: 1]. وَ﴿قُلْ أَعُوذُ بِرَبِّ النَّاسِ ﴾ [الناس: 1].\r\n', 'The proof for Seeking Refuge is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“Say: I seek refuge in the Lord of the Daybreak.” - [Surah Al-Falaq: 1] And:“Say: I seek refuge in the Lord of Mankind.”\r\n - [Surah An-Naas: 1]', 38),
(64, 3, 'وَفِي الْحَدِيثِ: (...وإِذَا اسْتَعَنْتَ فَاسْتَعِنْ بِاللهِ).\r\n', 'And in the hadeeth: \r\n\r\n“When you ask for assistance then seek assistance in Allaah.”\r\n', 37),
(65, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الاسْتِعَانَةِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿إِيَّاكَ نَعْبُدُ وإِيَّاكَ نَسْتَعِينُ﴾ [الفاتحة: 5].\r\n', 'The proof for Seeking Assistance is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“You alone do we worship and in You alone do we seek assistance.” \r\n- [Surah Al- Faatihah: 4]', 36),
(66, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الْخَشْيَةِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿فَلاَ تَخْشَوْهُمْ وَاخْشَوْنِي...﴾ الآية [البقرة: 150].\r\n', 'The proof for Repentance is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“And turn to your Lord in repentance and submit to Him [as Muslims].” \r\n- [Surah Az-Zumar: 54]', 34),
(67, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الرَّغْبَةِ، وَالرَّهْبَةِ، وَالْخُشُوعِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿إِنَّهُمْ كَانُوا يُسَارِعُونَ فِي الْخَيْرَاتِ وَيَدْعُونَنَا رَغَباً وَرَهَباً وَكَانُوا لَنَا خَاشِعِينَ ﴾ [الأنبياء: 90].\r\n', 'The proof for Longing and Dreading and Submissiveness is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n“Verily, they used to rush to do good deeds, and they would call on Us, longing (His reward) and dreading (His punishment), and they used to humble themselves submissively before Us.” \r\n- [Surah Al-Anbiyaa: 90]\r\n', 33),
(68, 3, 'وقوله: ﴿وَمَن يَتَوَكَّلْ عَلَى اللَّهِ فَهُوَ حَسْبُهُ﴾ [الطلاق: 3].', 'And (the meaning of) His saying:\r\n\r\n“And whoever relies upon Allaah, then He is sufficient for Him.” \r\n- [Surah At-Talaaq: 3]', 32),
(69, 3, 'ودَلِيلُ التَّوَكُلِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿وَعَلَى اللّهِ فَتَوَكَّلُواْ إِن كُنتُم مُّؤْمِنِينَ ﴾ [المائدة: 23].\r\n', 'The proof for Reliance is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:“And upon Allaah [alone] put your reliance if you are truly believers.” \r\n- [Surah Al- Maa`idah: 23]', 31),
(70, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الرَّجَاءِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿فَمَن كَانَ يَرْجُو لِقَاءَ رَبِّهِ فَلْيَعْمَلْ عَمَلاً صَالِحاً وَلاَ يُشْرِكْ بِعِبَادَةِ رَبِّهِ أَحَداً ﴾ [الكهف: 110].', 'The proof for Hope is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“So whoever hopes to meet his Lord, then let him perform righteous deeds, and not mix anyone into the worship of his Lord.” \r\n- [Surah Al-Kahf: 110]', 30),
(71, 3, 'وَدَلِيلُ الْخَوْفِ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿فَلاَ تَخَافُوهُمْ وَخَافُونِ إِن كُنتُم مُّؤْمِنِينَ ﴾ [آل عمران: 175].', 'The proof for fear is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:“So do not fear them, but fear Me if you are true believers.” \r\n- [Surah Aali ‘Imraan: 175]\r\n', 29),
(72, 3, 'وَفِي الْحَدِيثِ: ( الدُّعَاءُ مخ الْعِبَادَةِ ). وَالدَّلِيلُ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿وَقَالَ رَبُّكُمُ ادْعُونِي أَسْتَجِبْ لَكُمْ إِنَّ الَّذِينَ يَسْتَكْبِرُونَ عَنْ عِبَادَتِي سَيَدْخُلُونَ جَهَنَّمَ دَاخِرِينَ ﴾ [غافر: 60].\r\n', 'It is stated in a hadeeth: \r\n\r\n“The supplication is the core of worship.\r\n\r\n”The proof for this (i.e. supplication) is [the meaning of] Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“And your Lord says: ‘Supplicate to Me, I will respond to you. Verily those who are too proud to worship Me will enter the Hellfire in disgrace.`”\r\n - [Surah Ghaafir: 40]', 28),
(73, 3, 'فَمَنْ صَرَفَ مِنْهَا شَيْئًا لِغَيْرِ اللهِ؛ فَهُوَ مُشْرِكٌ كَافِرٌ؛ وَالدَّلِيلُ:\r\nقَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿وَمَن يَدْعُ مَعَ اللَّهِ إلٰهاً آخَرَ لاَ بُرْهَانَ لَهُ بِهِ فَإِنَّمَا حِسَابُهُ عِندَ رَبِّهِ إِنَّهُ لاَ يُفْلِحُ الْكَافِرُونَ ﴾ [المؤمنون: 117].', 'Anyone who directs any part of that to anyone besides Allaah, then he is a mushrik (polytheist) kaafir (disbeliever).\r\n\r\nThe proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“And whoever calls unto another god besides Allaah, of which he has no proof for, his reckoning is only with his Lord.  Surely, the disbelievers will not be successful.”  \r\n- [Surah Al-Mu`minoon: 117]', 27),
(74, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ: قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿وَأَنَّ الْمَسَاجِدَ لِلَّهِ فَلاَ تَدْعُوا مَعَ اللَّهِ أَحَداً ﴾ [الجن: 18].\r\n', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“And the masaajid belong to Allaah, so do not call unto anyone along with Allaah.” \r\n- [Surah Al-Jinn: 18]', 26);
INSERT INTO `pages` (`pageid`, `book_id`, `content_arabic`, `content_english`, `page_number`) VALUES
(75, 3, 'وَأَنْوَاعُ الْعِبَادَةِ الَّتِي أَمَرَ اللهُ بِهَا مِثْلُ: الإِسْلامِ، وَالإِيمَانِ، وَالإِحْسَانِ، وَمِنْهُ: الدُّعَاءُ، وَالْخَوْفُ، وَالرَّجَاءُ، وَالتَّوَكُّلُ، وَالرَّغْبَةُ، وَالرَّهْبَةُ، وَالْخُشُوعُ، وَالْخَشْيَةُ، وَالإِنَابَةُ، وَالاسْتِعَانَةُ، وَالاسْتِعَاذَةُ، وَالاسْتِغَاثَةُ، وَالذَّبْحُ، وَالنَّذْرُ، وَغَيْرُ ذَلكَ مِنْ أَنْوَاعِ الْعِبَادَةِ الَّتِي أَمَرَ اللهُ بِهَا. كُلُّهَا للهِ تَعَالَى.\r\n', 'The types of worship that Allaah commanded, such as Islaam, Eemaan and Ihsaan, which includes: Supplication, Fear, Hope, Reliance, Longing, Dreading, Submissiveness, Awe, Repentance, Seeking Assistance, Seeking Refuge, Asking for Help, Offering Sacrifices and Making Oaths, and all of the other types of worship that Allaah commanded – all of these belong to Allaah, alone.', 25),
(76, 3, 'قَالَ ابْنُ كَثِيرٍ ـ رَحِمَهُ اللهُ تَعَالَى: \r\nالخَالِقُ لِهَذِهِ الأَشْيَاءَ هُوَ الْمُسْتَحِقُّ لِلْعِبَادَةِ.\r\n', 'Ibn Kather, may Allaah have mercy on him, said:\r\n\r\n“The creator of these things is the One who truly deserves to be worshipped.”', 24),
(77, 3, 'وَالرَّبُ هُوَ الْمَعْبُودُ، \r\nوَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿يَا أَيُّهَا النَّاسُ اعْبُدُواْ رَبَّكُمُ الَّذِي خَلَقَكُمْ وَالَّذِينَ مِن قَبْلِكُمْ لَعَلَّكُمْ تَتَّقُونَ * الَّذِي جَعَلَ لَكُمُ الأَرْضَ فِرَاشاً وَالسَّمَآء بِنَآءً وَأَنزَلَ مِنَ السَّمَآءِ مَآءً فَأَخْرَجَ بِهِ مِنَ الثَّمَرَاتِ رِزْقاً لَّكُمْ فَلاَ تَجْعَلُواْ لِلّهِ أَندَاداً وَأَنتُمْ تَعْلَمُونَ ﴾ [البقرة: 21، 22]\r\n', 'The word Rabb (Lord) means One who is worshipped. The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“O mankind! Worship your Lord who created you and those before you, so that you may be dutiful to Him. He is the One who made the earth a resting place for you, and the sky as a canopy, and sent down water from the sky and brought forth therewith fruits as a provision for you. So do no set up rivals with Allaah in worship knowingly.” \r\n\r\n- [Surah Al-Baqarah: 21-22]', 23),
(78, 3, 'وَقَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: \r\n﴿إِنَّ رَبَّكُمُ اللّهُ الَّذِي خَلَقَ السَّمَاوَاتِ وَالأَرْضَ فِي سِتَّةِ أَيَّامٍ ثُمَّ اسْتَوَى عَلَى الْعَرْشِ يُغْشِي اللَّيْلَ النَّهَارَ يَطْلُبُهُ حَثِيثاً وَالشَّمْسَ وَالْقَمَرَ وَالنُّجُومَ مُسَخَّرَاتٍ بِأَمْرِهِ أَلاَ لَهُ الْخَلْقُ وَالأَمْرُ تَبَارَكَ اللّهُ رَبُّ الْعَالَمِينَ﴾ [الأعراف: 54].', 'And (the meaning of) His statement:“Verily, your Lord is Allaah, who created the heavens and the earth in six days, and then rose over the Throne. He brings the night as a cover over the day, which it follows rapidly. And He made the sun, the moon and the stars subjected to His Command. Surely, to Him belongs the Creation and the Command. Blessed is Allaah, Lord of the Worlds.” \r\n- [Surah Al-A`raaf: 54]', 22),
(79, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿وَمِنْ آيَاتِهِ اللَّيْلُ وَالنَّهَارُ وَالشَّمْسُ وَالْقَمَرُ لاَ تَسْجُدُوا لِلشَّمْسِ وَلاَ لِلْقَمَرِ وَاسْجُدُوا لِلَّهِ الَّذِي خَلَقَهُنَّ إِن كُنتُمْ إِيَّاهُ تَعْبُدُونَ﴾ [فصلت: 37].\r\n', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s statement:“And from among His signs are the night and the day, and the sun and the moon. Do not prostrate yourselves to the sun or to the moon, but rather prostrate yourselves to Allaah who created them, if it is He whom you truly worship. \r\n- [Surah Fussilat: 37]\r\n', 21),
(80, 3, 'فَإِذَا قِيلَ لَكَ: بِمَ عَرَفْتَ رَبَّكَ؟ فَقُلْ: \r\nبِآيَاتِهِ وَمَخْلُوقَاتِهِ، وَمِنْ آيَاتِهِ: اللَّيْلُ، وَالنَّهَارُ، وَالشَّمْسُ، وَالْقَمَرُ، وَمِنْ مَخْلُوقَاتِهِ السَّمَاوَاتُ السَّبْعُ وَالأَرَضُونَ السَّبْعُ وَمَنْ فِيهِنَّ، وَمَا بَيْنَهُمَا؛\r\n', 'So if it is said to you: How did you come to know of your Lord? Then say: \r\n\r\nBy way of His signs and His creations. And among His signs are the night and the day, and the sun and the moon. And among His creations are the seven (levels of) heaven and the seven (levels of) earth, as well as whoever [and whatever] lies in them and between them.', 20),
(81, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿الْحَمْدُ للَََّهِ رَبِّ الْعَالَمِينَ﴾ [الفاتحة: 2].\r\nوَكُلُّ مَنْ سِوَى اللهِ عَالَمٌ، وَأَنَا وَاحِدٌ مِنْ ذَلِكَ الْعَالَمِ.', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s statement:\r\n\r\n“All praise be to Allaah, Lord of the ‘Alameen [i.e. all of creation].” \r\n[Surah Al-Faatihah: 1]\r\n\r\nThe word ‘Aalam refers to everything apart from Allaah, and I am part of that creation.', 19),
(82, 3, 'فَإِذَا قِيلَ لَكَ: مَنْ رَبُّكَ؟ فَقُلْ: رَبِّيَ اللهُ الَّذِي رَبَّانِي، وَرَبَّى جَمِيعَ الْعَالَمِينَ بِنِعَمِهِ، وَهُوَ مَعْبُودِي لَيْسَ لِي مَعْبُودٌ سِوَاهُ؛.\r\n', 'So if it is said: Who is your Lord? Then say: My Lord is Allaah, the One who nurtured me and nurtured all of creation through His favours. And He is the One whom I worship, there being to me no (false) deity worshipped that is equal to Him.\r\n', 18),
(83, 3, 'فَإِذَا قِيلَ لَكَ: مَا الأُصُولُ الثَّلاثَةُ التِي يَجِبُ عَلَى الإِنْسَانِ مَعْرِفَتُهَا؟ فَقُلْ: مَعْرِفَةُ الْعَبْدِ رَبَّهُ، وَدِينَهُ، وَنَبِيَّهُ مُحَمَّدًا صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ.', 'So if it said to you: What are the three fundamental principles that mankind is obligated to know? Then say: That the servant knows his Lord, his Religion and his Prophet Muhammad, (may the peace and blessings of Allaah be on him).\r\n', 17),
(84, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى ﴿وَاعْبُدُواْ اللّهَ وَلاَ تُشْرِكُواْ بِهِ شَيْئ﴾\r\n[النساء: 36].\r\n', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s statement:\r\n\r\n“And worship Allaah [alone] and do not mix anything [in worship] with Him.” \r\n- [Surah An-Nisaa: 36]', 16),
(85, 3, 'وَأَعْظَمُ مَا أَمَرَ اللهُ بِهِ التَّوْحيِدُ، وَهُوَ: إِفْرَادُ اللهِ بِالْعِبَادَةِ. وَأَعْظَمُ مَا نَهَى عَنْه الشِّركُ، وَهُوَ: دَعْوَةُ غَيْرِهِ مَعَهُ،\r\n', 'The greatest thing that Allaah commanded is Tawheed, which means: Singling Allaah out in worship. And the greatest thing that Allaah warned against is Shirk, which is: Supplicating to others along with Him.', 15),
(86, 3, 'كَمَا قَالَ تَعَالَى: ﴿ وَمَا خَلَقْتُ الْجِنَّ وَالإِنْسَ إِلاَّ لِيَعْبُدُونِ ﴾ [ الذاريات: 56]. \r\nوَمَعْنَى ﴿يَعْبُدُونِ﴾ : يُوَحِّدُونِ', 'As (in the meaning of what) He says:\r\n\r\n“And I did not create the Jinn and mankind except to worship Me.” \r\n- [Surah Adh-Dhaariyaat: 56] \r\n\r\nThe meaning of “to worship Me” is “to single Allaah out [in worship].”\r\n', 14),
(87, 3, 'اعْلَمْ أَرْشَدَكَ اللهُ لِطَاعَتِهِ، أَنَّ الْحَنِيفِيَّةَ مِلَّةَ إِبْرَاهِيمَ: أَنْ تَعْبُدَ اللهَ وَحْدَهُ، مُخْلِصًا لَهُ الدِّينَ. وَبِذَلِكَ أَمَرَ اللهُ جَمِيعَ النَّاسِ، وَخَلَقَهُمْ لَهَا؛\r\n', 'Know, may Allaah grant you the ability to obey Him, that Al-Haneefiyyah, the Religion of Ibraaheem, is that you worship Allaah alone, making the religion sincerely [i.e. solely] for Him. This is what Allaah ordered all of mankind to do, and this is the purpose for which He created them\r\n', 13),
(88, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿ لاَ تَجِدُ قَوْماً يُؤْمِنُونَ بِاللَّهِ وَالْيَوْمِ الآخِرِ يُوَادُّونَ مَنْ حَادَّ اللَّهَ وَرَسُولَهُ وَلَوْ كَانُوا آبَاءَهُمْ أَوْ أَبْنَاءهُمْ أَوْ إِخْوَانَهُمْ أَوْ عَشِيرَتَهُمْ أُوْلَئِكَ كَتَبَ فِي قُلُوبِهِمُ الإِيمَانَ وَأَيَّدَهُم بِرُوحٍ مِّنْهُ وَيُدْخِلُهُمْ جَنَّاتٍ تَجْرِي مِن تَحْتِهَا الأَنْهَارُ خَالِدِينَ فِيهَا رَضِيَ  اللَّهُ عَنْهُمْ وَرَضُوا عَنْهُ أُوْلَئِكَ حِزْبُ اللَّهِ أَلاَ إِنَّ حِزْبَ اللَّهِ هُمُ الْمُفْلِحُونَ ﴾ \r\n[المجادلة: 22].\r\n', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\n“You will not find any people who believe in Allaah and the Last Day making friendship with those who oppose Allaah and His Messenger, even if they are their fathers or their sons or their brothers or there kindred. For such He has written Faith in their hearts, and strengthened them with Rooh (light and guidance) from Himself. And He will admit them into Gardens under which rivers flow to dwell therein forever. Allah is pleased with them and they with Him. They are the party of Allaah. Verily it is the party of Allaah that will be the successful”. \r\n- [Surah Al-Mujaadilah: 22]', 12),
(89, 3, 'الثَّالِثَةُ: أَنَّ مَنْ أَطَاعَ الرَّسُولَ، وَوَحَّدَ اللهَ لا يَجُوزُ لَهُ مُوَالاةُ مَنْ حَادَّ اللهَ وَرَسُولَهُ، وَلَوْ كَانَ أَقْرَبَ قَرِيبٍ؛\r\n', 'Third: Whoever obeys the Messenger [i.e. Muhammad] and singles Allaah out [in worship], it is not permissible for him to take as allies those who oppose Allaah and His Messenger, not even if they are close relatives.\r\n', 11),
(90, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿وَأَنَّ الْمَسَاجِدَ لِلَّهِ فَلاَ تَدْعُوا مَعَ اللَّهِ أَحَداً ﴾ \r\n[الجن: 18].', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of Allaah`s statement):“And verily the masaajid belong to Allaah, so do not call unto anyone along with Allaah.” - \r\n[Surah Al-Jinn: 18]', 10),
(91, 3, 'الثَّانِيَةُ: أَنَّ الله لا يَرْضَى أَنْ يُشْرَكَ مَعَهُ أَحَدُ فِي عِبَادَتِهِ، لا مَلَكٌ مُقَرَّبٌ، وَلا نَبِيٌّ مُرْسَلٌ؛', 'Second: Allaah is not pleased with anyone being mixed into worship with Him – neither an angel brought close nor a prophet that was sent.\r\n', 9),
(92, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى: ﴿إِنَّا أَرْسَلْنَا إِلَيْكُمْ رَسُولاً شَاهِداً عَلَيْكُمْ كَمَا أَرْسَلْنَا إِلَى فِرْعَوْنَ رَسُولاً * فَعَصَى فِرْعَوْنُ الرَّسُولَ فَأَخَذْنَاهُ أَخْذاً وبيلا﴾ \r\n[المزمل: 15، 16].', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s statement:\r\n“Verily, We sent to you a Messenger, to be a witness over you, just as we sent a Messenger to Pharaoh. But Pharaoh disobeyed the Messenger [i.e. Moosaa] so We seized him with a severe punishment” - [Surah Al-Muzzammil: 15-16]', 8),
(93, 3, 'الأُولَى: أَنَّ اللهَ خَلَقَنَا، وَرَزَقَنَا، وَلَمْ يَتْرُكْنَا هَمَلا، بَلْ أَرْسَلَ إِلَيْنَا رَسُولاً، فَمَنْ أَطَاعَهُ دَخَلَ الجَنَّةَ، وَمَنْ عَصَاهُ دَخَلَ النَّارَ،', 'First: That Allaah created us, provided sustenance for us, and did not leave us neglected. Rather, He sent a Messenger to us. So whoever obeys him will enter Paradise, whereas whoever disobeys him will enter the Hellfire.', 7),
(94, 3, 'اعْلَمْ رَحِمَكَ اللهُ أَنَّه يَجِبُ عَلَى كُلِّ مُسْلِمٍ وَمُسْلِمَةٍ، تَعَلُّمُ ثَلاثِ هَذِهِ الْمَسَائِل، والْعَمَلُ بِهِنَّ:', 'Know, may Allaah have mercy on you, that it is obligatory upon every Muslim male and female to learn and act upon the following three things:', 6),
(95, 3, 'وَقَالَ البُخَارِيُّ ـ رَحِمَهُ اللهُ تَعَالَى ـ: بَابٌ: العِلْمُ قَبْلَ القَوْلِ وَالْعَمَلِ؛\r\n وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى:\r\n ﴿فَاعْلَمْ أَنَّهُ لاَ إِلَٰه إِلاَّ اللَّهُ وَاسْتَغْفِرْ لِذَنبِكَ﴾ [محمد:19]\r\n، فَبَدَأَ بِالْعِلْمِ (قَبْلَ القَوْلِ وَالعَمَلِ)\r\n', 'Al-Bukhaaree, may Allaah have mercy on him, said: \r\nChapter: “Knowledge comes before speech and action”.\r\n\r\nThe proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n“So know  that there is no deity worthy of worship except Allaah, and seek forgiveness for your sins”. - [Surah Muhammad: 19] \r\n\r\nSo He began by mentioning knowledge before speech and action.', 5),
(96, 3, 'قَالَ الشَّافِعيُّ ـ رَحِمَهُ اللهُ تَعَالَى ـ: لَوْ مَا أَنْزَلَ اللهُ حُجَّةً عَلَى خَلْقِهِ إِلا هَذِهِ السُّورَةَ لَكَفَتْهُمْ.\r\n', 'Ash-Shaafi`ee, may Allaah have mercy on him, said: “Had Allaah not sent down a proof to His creation other than this surah (chapter), it would have been sufficient for them”.', 4),
(97, 3, 'وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى:\r\nبسم الله الرحمن الرحيم\r\n﴿وَالْعَصْرِ - إِنَّ الأِنْسَانَ لَفِي خُسْرٍ - إِلّا الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا وَعَمِلُوا الصَّالِحَاتِ وَتَوَاصَوْا بِالْحَقِّ وَتَوَاصَوْا بِالصَّبْرِ﴾ - [ سورة العصر ] \r\n', 'The proof for this is (the meaning of) Allaah`s saying:\r\n\r\nIn the Name of Allaah, the Most Merciful, the Bestower of Mercy.\r\n\r\n“By the time! - Verily mankind is at loss – except for those who believe and perform righteous deeds, and advise one another towards the truth and advise one another towards patience”. - [Surah Al-`Asr]', 3),
(98, 3, 'بسم الله الرحمان الرحيم - اعْلمْ رَحِمَكَ اللهُ أَنَّهُ يَجِبُ عَلَيْنَا تَعَلُّمُ أَرْبَعِ مَسَائِلَ:', 'In the Name of Allaah, the Most Merciful, the Bestower of Mercy.  Know, may Allaah have mercy on you, that we are obligated to learn four matters:', 1),
(99, 3, 'الأُولَى: الْعِلْمُ: وَهُوَ مَعْرِفَةُ اللهِ، وَمَعْرِفَةُ نَبِيِّهِ ـ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ ـ، وَمَعْرِفَةُ دِينِ الإِسْلامِ بالأَدِلَّةِ.\r\nالثَّانِيَةُ: الْعَمَلُ بِهِ\r\nالثَّالِثَةُ: الدَّعْوَةُ إِلَيْهِ\r\nالرَّابِعَةُ: الصَّبْرُ عَلَى الأَذَى فِيهِ.', 'First: Knowledge, which means: awareness of Allaah, awareness of His Prophet, and awareness of the Religion of Islaam, based on evidences.  \r\n\r\nSecond: Acting on this.  \r\n\r\nThird: Calling to it.  \r\n\r\nFourth: Patience with the harm that befalls due to it.', 2),
(103, 2, 'والنارُ يَصلاها الشقيُّ بحكمةٍ ** وكذا التقيُّ إلى الجِنانِ سيدخلُ', ' And the wretched one will be burned in the Fire by Divine wisdom - And likewise (by Divine wisdom) the pious one will enter Gardens.', 13),
(104, 2, 'وكذا الصراطُ يُمَدُّ فَوْقَ جَهَنِّمٍ ** فمُسلمٌ نَـاجٍ وآخـرُ مُهمـلُ', ' And likewise (I affirm) the Bridge extended over Hellfire (over which all will pass) - So (either) one made safe (and) delivered (or) another forsaken (who will fall).', 12),
(105, 2, 'وأُقِرُّ بالميزانِ و الحـوضِ الذي ** أَرْجُو بِأنِّي منه رِيَّـاً أنهـلُ', ' And I affirm the Scales and the Pool which - I hope to be (amongst those) whose thirst will be quenched (by it).', 11),
(106, 2, 'و المـؤمنون يَرَوْنَ حقَّـاً رَبَّهُـم ** وإلى السماءِ بِغيْرِ كيْفٍ يَنْزِلُ', '  And the Believers will see their Lord in Truth (in the Hereafter) - And to the heaven does He descend without (designating) a how.', 10),
(107, 2, 'قبْحَاً لِمَنْ نَبَذَ القـرآن وراءهُ ** وإذا أستدلَّ يقول قال الأخْطَلُ', ' Disgrace for the one who threw the Qur''aan behind his back - And when asked to provide evidence, says, "al-Akhtal [the Christian] said!"', 9),
(108, 2, 'و أَردُّ عهدتَهـا إلـى نُقّالِهـا ** وأَصونها عَنْ كُلِ ما يُتَخيّـلُ\r\n', ' And I return the obligatory responsibility towards them to those who transmitted them (intact) - And I protect them from all that is imagined (with respect to their realities).', 8),
(109, 2, 'وجميعُ آياتِ الصفاتِ أُمِرُّهَـا ** حَقَّاً كما نَقَـلَ الطِّـرازُ الأَوَّلُ', ' And all the verses of the attributes I pass them on - In truth, just as the first (and best of generations) have transmitted [without explaining them away].', 7),
(110, 2, 'وأقولُ قالَ اللهُ جـلَّ جلالُـهُ ** والمُصْطفى الهادي وَلا أَتأَوَّلُ', ' And I say, "Allaah, the Mighty and Majestic said" - [And likewise] "the Chosen One (the Prophet) [said]," and I do not explain away (their speech).', 6),
(111, 2, 'وأقول في القرآن ما جاءت بِهِ ** آياتُهُ فَهـو الكريم الُمنْـزَلُ', ' And I say regarding the Qur''an (only) that which has come - [In its] verses, for it is the Noble Revelation.', 5),
(112, 2, 'وَلِكُلّهم قـدرٌ عَـلا وَفَضائِـلٌ** لكِنَّما الصِّديقُ مِنْهـم أَفْضَـلُ', ' And every one of them has a station and a shining excellence - However, amongst them [Abu Bakr] al-Siddeeq is the most excellent.', 4),
(113, 2, 'حُبُّ الصحابةِ كُلِّهِم لي مذهبٌ ** ومودةُ القربى بِهـا أَتَوسّـلُ', ' Loving the Companions, all of them (without exception) is for me a (school of) doctrine - And love of the nearest ones (the Ahl al-Bayt) do I seek as a means of nearness (to Allaah)', 3),
(114, 2, 'اسمع كلامَ مُحَقِّقٍ في قوله ** لا ينْثنـي عنـهُ ولاَ يتبـدّلُ\r\n', 'Listen to the speech of one who has ascertained the truth of his statement - Without departing from it nor replacing it (with something else)', 2),
(115, 2, 'يا سائِلي عَنْ مَذْهَبي وعَقيدَتي ** رُزِقَ الهُدَى مَنْ لِلْهِدايَةِ يسألُ\r\n', 'O one who asks about my doctrine and creed - Certainly, bestowed with guidance is he who asks for guidance.', 1),
(116, 1, 'ومن السنة : \r\nما ثبت في الصحيح عن ابي موسى رضي الله عنه عن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم : \r\n( مثل ما بعثني الله به من الهدى والعلم كمثل الغيث الكثير أصاب أرضاً ، فكان منها نقية قبلت الماء فأنبتت الكلأ والعشب الكثير ، وكانت منها أجادب أمسكت الماء فنفع الله به الناس فشربوا وسقوا وزرعوا ، واصاب منها طائفة أخرى إنما هي قيعان لا تمسك الماء ولا تنبت كلأ ، فذلك مثل من فقه في دين الله ونفعه ما بعثني الله به فعلم وعلّم ، ومثل من لم يرفع بذلك راساً ولم يقبل هدى الله الذي أرسلت به ) .', 'And from the Sunnah from what has been established in the Saheeh from Aboo Musaa, may Allah be pleased with him, from the Prophet (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam) who said: \r\n“The example of guidance and knowledge with which Allah has sent me is like abundant rain falling on the earth, some of which was fertile soil that absorbed rain water and brought forth vegetation and grass in abundance. Another portion of it was hard and held the rain water and Allah benefited the people with it and they utilised it for drinking, making their animals drink from it and for irrigation of the land for cultivation. And a portion of it was barren which could neither hold the water nor bring forth vegetation. The first is the example of the person who comprehends Allah`s religion and gets benefit which Allah has revealed through me and learns and then teaches others. The last example is that of a person who does not care for it and does not take Allah`s guidance revealed through me.”', 38),
(117, 1, '  وقوله تعالى : \r\n{ إنهم كانوا إذا قيل لهم لا إله إلا الله يستكبرون * ويقولون أإنا لتاركوا ءالهتنا لشاعر مجنون } .', 'And (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“Indeed they used to behave arrogantly when it was said to them Laa Ilaha Illa Allah. They would say, “Should we leave off our gods to follow a crazy poet?”', 37),
(118, 1, 'ودليل القبول : قوله تعالى : \r\n{ وكذلك ما أرسلنا من قبلك في قرية من نذير إلا قال مترفوها إنا وجدنا ءاباءنا على أمة وإنا على ءاثارهم مقتدون * قال أولوا جئتكم بأهدى مما وجدتم عليه ءاباءكم قالوا إنا بما أرسلتم به كافرون * فانتقمنا منهم فانظر كيف كان عاقبة المكذبين }', 'And the evidence concerning al-Qubool (acceptance) is (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“And likewise We did not send before you in any village one who would warn except that its affluent would say, “Indeed we found our fathers upon a certain way and we will continue to be upon their way.” The one warning said, “Even if I bring to you all that which contains more guidance than what you found your father upon?” They said, “Indeed we do not believe in what you have been sent.” Therefore We took revenge of them so look at the consequence of those who denied.”', 36),
(119, 1, 'وهذا هو تمام الانقياد وغايته .\r\n', 'And this in fact is complete submission and its main focus.', 35),
(120, 1, 'ومن السنة : قوله صلى الله عليه وسلم : ( لا يؤمن أحدكم حتى يكون هواه تبعاً لما جئت به )', 'And from the Sunnah is his statement (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam) :\r\n“None of you truly believe until one`s desires follow what I have brought.”', 34),
(121, 1, ' وقوله تعالى : \r\n{ فلا وربك لا يؤمنون حتى يحكموك فيما شجر بينهم ثم لا يجدوا في انفسهم حرجاً مما قضيت ويسلموا تسليماً } .', 'And (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“No by your Lord they will not believe until you passed judgment for them in their disputes then they will not find in themselves harm in what you have decreed and they submit whole heartedly.”', 33),
(122, 1, 'أي بـ " لا إله إلا الله"\r\n', 'Here al-‘Urwah al-Wuthqaa means Laa Ilaha Illa Allah.', 32),
(123, 1, 'وقوله : { ومن يسلم وجهه لله وهو محسن فقد استمسك بالعروة الوثقى }\r\n', 'And (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“And whosoever submits himself to Allah and does good deeds has held onto al-‘Urwah al-Wuthqaa”', 31),
(124, 1, 'وقوله : { ومن أحسن ديناً ممن أسلم وجهه لله وهو محسن }', 'And (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“And whoever perfects his religion from whomsoever has submitted himself to Allah while doing good deeds.”', 30),
(125, 1, 'ودليل الانقياد : ما دل عليه قوله تعالى : \r\n{ وأنيبوا إلى ربكم وأسلموا من قبل أن ياتيكم العذاب ثم لا تنصرون }\r\n', 'And the evidence concerning al-Inqiyaad (submission) is based on His Statement:\r\n“Repent to your Lord and submit to Him”', 29),
(126, 1, 'ومن السنة : ما ثبت في الصحيح عن أنس رضي الله عنه ، قال : \r\n( قال رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم : ثلاث من كن فيه وجد حلاوة الإيمان : أن يكون الله ورسوله أحب إليه مما سواهما ، وأن يحب المرء لا يحبه إلا لله ، وأن يكره ان يعود في الكفر بعد إذ أنقذه الله منه كما يكره أن يقذف في النار ) .', 'And from the Sunnah is what is established in the Saheeh from Anas, may Allah be pleased with him who said that the Messenger of Allah (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam) said:\r\n“There are three ofwhom the sweetness of faith can be found within them they are the one whom Allah and His Messenger are more beloved to him than anything else, the one who loves a person for the sake of Allah, and the one who hates to return to disbelief after Allah had saved him from it just as he would hate to be thrown in the hellfire.”', 28),
(127, 1, 'وقوله : \r\n{ يأيها الذين ءامنوا من يرتد منكم عن دينه فسوف يأتي الله بقوم يحبهم ويحبونه أذلة على المؤمنين أعزة على الكافرين يجاهدون في سبيل الله ولا يخافون لومة لائم } .', 'And (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“O` You who believe whoever apostates from amongst you from his religion then Allah will bring a people whom He will love and they will love Him, being kind with the believers and harsh upon the disbelievers, fighting in the path of Allah and not fearing the blame of those who find fault (with others).”', 27),
(128, 1, 'ودليل المحبة : قوله تعالى : \r\n{ ومن الناس من يتخذ من دون الله أنداداً يحبونهم كحب الله والذين ءامنوا أشد حباً لله }', 'And the evidence concerning al-Mahabbah (love) is (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“And amongst mankind are those who take other than Allah as partners loving them as they love Allah but those who believe are strict in their love to Allah (Alone).”', 26),
(129, 1, 'ومن السنة : ما ثبت في الصحيحين عن معاذ بن جبل رضي الله عنه عن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم :\r\n( ما من أحد يشهد أن لا إله إلا الله وأن محمداً رسول الله ، صادقاً من قلبه ، إلا حرمه الله على النار ) .', 'And from the Sunnah is what has been established from the two Saheehs from Mu`adh bin Jabal, may Allah be pleased with him, that the Prophet (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam) said:\r\n“There is not one person who testifies that there is nothing worthy of worship except for Allah and that Muhammad is His Servant and Messenger honestly within his heart except that Allah will forbid him from the hellfire.”', 25),
(130, 1, 'وقوله تعالى : \r\n{ ومن الناس من يقول ءامنا بالله واليوم الآخر وما هم بمؤمنين * يخادعون الله والذين ءامنوا وما يخدعون إلا أنفسهم وما يشعرون * في قلوبهم مرض فزادهم الله مرضاً ولهم عذاب أليم بما كانوا يكذبون } .', 'And (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement: \r\n“And from amongst mankind are those who say we believe in Allah and in the Last Day but they are not really believers. They seek to deceive Allah and those who believe but they only are deceiving themselves while not even realizing it. In their hearts is a disease and Allah increases their disease and they will have a painful punishment for what they pretended about.”', 24),
(131, 1, 'ودليل الصدق : قوله تعالى : \r\n{ الم * أحسب الناس أن يتركوا أن يقولوا ءامنا وهم لا يفتنون * ولقد فتنا الذين من قبلهم فليعلمن الله الذين صدقوا وليعلمن الكاذببين }', 'And the evidence concerning as-Sidq (honesty) is (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“Alif Laam Meem. Do the people think that they will be left alone to say that they believe and that they will not be tested? Indeed We tested those before them Allah surely knows those who believe and He knows those who pretend.”', 23),
(132, 1, 'وللنسائي في " اليوم والليلة "من حديث رجلين من الصحابة عن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم : ( من قال لا إله إلا الله وحده لا شريك له ، له الملك ، وله الحمد ، وهو على كل شيء قدير ، مخلصاً بها من قلبه ، يصدق بها لسانه . . . إلا فتق الله السماء فتقاً ، حتى ينظر إلى قائلها من أهل الأرض ، وحق لعبد نظر إليه الله أن يعطيه سؤله ) .', 'And from an-Nisaa`ee in (his book) al-Yawm wal-Laylah from the narration of two of the companions from the Prophet (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam): \r\n“Whoever says Laa Ilaha Illa Allah Wahdahu Laa Shareeka Lah lahul-Mulk wa lahul-Hamd wa Huwa ‘alaa kulli shayin Qadeer (There is nothing worthy of worship except for Allah Alone, He does not have any partner, to Him belongs the dominion and to Him is all praise. He is Able to do all things) sincerely in one`s heart affirming what was uttered by the tongue then Allah will tear a hole in the heavens to look at the one who said it from amongst the inhabitants of earth and the right given to the servant is that Allah will look to him and gives him what he asks for.”', 22),
(133, 1, 'وفي الصحيح عن عتبان بن مالك رضي الله عنه عن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم : \r\n( إن الله حرم على النار من قال لا إله إلا الله يبتغي بذلك وجه الله عز وجل )', 'And from an-Nisaa`ee in (his book) al-Yawm wal-Laylah from the narration of two of the companions from the Prophet (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam): \r\n“Whoever says Laa Ilaha Illa Allah Wahdahu Laa Shareeka Lah lahul-Mulk wa lahul-Hamd wa Huwa ‘alaa kulli shayin Qadeer (There is nothing worthy of worship except for Allah Alone, He does not have any partner, to Him belongs the dominion and to Him is all praise. He is Able to do all things) sincerely in one`s heart affirming what was uttered by the tongue then Allah will tear a hole in the heavens to look at the one who said it from amongst the inhabitants ofearth and the right given to the servant is that Allah will look to him and gives him what he asks for.”', 21),
(134, 1, 'ومن السنة : الحديث الثابت في الصحيح عن أبي هريرة رضي الله عنه عن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم : ( أسعد الناس بشفاعتي من قال لاإله إلا الله خالصاً من قلبه -أو من نفسه - )', 'And from the Sunnah is the established narration in the Saheeh from Aboo Hurayrah (radiAllahu anhum) from the Prophet (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam): \r\n“The happiest people to receive my intercession are those who said Laa Ilaha Illa Allah (there is nothing worthy of worship except for Allah) sincerely from one`s heart  or soul.”', 20),
(135, 1, 'وقوله سبحانه : \r\n{ وما من أمروا إلا ليعبدوا الله مخلصين له الدين حنفاء } .', 'And (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“They were only ordered to worship Allah sincerely for Him and worship none but Him Alone.”', 19),
(136, 1, 'ودليل الإخلاص : قوله تعالى : { ألا لله الدين الخالص }', 'And the evidence concerning al-Ikhlaas (sincerity) is (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement: “Is not the pure religion to Allah?”', 18),
(137, 1, 'وعن أبي هريرة أيضاً من حديث طويل : ( من لقيت من وراء هذا الحائط يشهد أن لا إله إلا الله مستيقناً بها من قلبه فبشره بالجنة )', 'And also the long narration of Aboo Hurayrah:\r\n“Whoever I meet behind this wall testifying that there is nothing worthy or worship except for Allah with full conviction of it in his heart then give him the glad tidings of paradise.”', 17),
(138, 1, 'وفي رواية : ( لا يلقى الله بهما عبد غير شاك فيحجب عن الجنة ) .\r\n', 'And in another narrative:\r\n“Not holding by Allah by them both without doubt that he will be covered in the paradise.”', 16),
(139, 1, 'ومن السنة : الحديث الثابت في الصحيح عن أبي هريرة رضي الله عنه ، قال : ( قال رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم :\r\nأشهد أن لا إله إلا الله وأني رسول الله ، لا يلقى الله بهما عبد غير شاك فيهما إلا دخل الجنة )', 'And from the Sunnah is the established narration in the Saheeh from Aboo Hurayrah (radiAllahu anhum) that he mentioned the Messenger of Allah (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam) saying:“I bear witness that nothing has the right to be worshipped except for Allah and that I am the Messenger of Allah not holding Allah by them both to be without doubt in the two testimonies except that he will enter paradise”.', 15),
(140, 1, 'فاشترط في صدق إيمانهم بالله ورسوله كونهم لم يرتابوا -أي لم يشكوا - فأما المرتاب فهو من المنافقين .', 'So it is stipulated concerning the honesty of their faith in Allah and His Messenger that they did not falter meaning that they did not cast doubts. As for the one who doubts then he is from the Munaafiqoon (the Hypocrites).', 14),
(141, 1, 'ودليل اليقين : قوله تعالى : { إنما المؤمنون الذين ءامنوا بالله ورسوله ثم لم يرتابوا وجاهدوا باموالهم وأنفسهم في سبيل الله أولئك هم الصادقون }', 'And the evidence concerning al-Yaqeen (certainty) is (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement: \r\n\r\n“The believers are those who believe in Allah and His Messenger then they do not doubt it and they strive with their wealth and with their souls in the path of Allah they are those who believe with certainty.”', 13),
(142, 1, 'ومن السنة : الحديث الثابت في الصحيح عن عثمان رضي الله عنه قال : \r\n( قال رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم : من مات وهو يعلم أنه لا إله إلا الله دخل الجنة ) .', 'And from the Sunnah is the established narration in the Saheeh from ‘Uthmaan, Allah be pleased with him, who said that the Messenger of Allah (sallallahu alayhi wa sallam) said:\r\n            \r\n“Whoever dies knowing that there is nothing worthy or worship except for Allah will enter paradise.”', 12),
(143, 1, 'أي بـ " لا إله إلا الله " { وهم يعلمون } بقلوبهم مانطقوا به بألسنتهم .', 'This “truth” is referring to Laa Ilaha Illa Allah.  “...And they know” What is in their hearts which is pronounced by their tongues.', 11),
(144, 1, 'السابع : القبول المنافي للرد .', 'Seven: al-Qubool (acceptance) which negates rejection.', 7),
(145, 1, 'وقوله : { إلا من شهد بالحق وهم يعلمون }', 'And (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement:\r\n“...Except for the one who testifies to the truth and they know.”', 10),
(146, 1, 'دليل العلم : قوله تعالى : { فأعلم أنه لا إله إلا الله }', 'The evidence concerning al-‘Ilm (knowledge) is (the translation of the meaning of) His Statement: \r\n“Know that there is nothing worthy or worship except for Allah.”', 9),
(147, 1, 'أدلة هذه الشروط من كتاب الله تعالى ومن سنة رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم :', 'Evidences that these conditions are from the Book of Allah Most High and the Sunnah of the Messenger of Allah peace be upon him.', 8),
(148, 1, 'السادس : الانقياد لحقوقها ، وهي : الأعمال الواجبة ، إخلاصاً لله ، وطلباً لمرضاته .', 'Six: al-Inqiyaad (submission) to its rights and it is to do the obligatory deeds sincerely for Allah seeking His Pleasure.', 6),
(149, 1, 'الخامس : المحبة لهذه الكلمة ، ولما دلت عليه ، والسرور بذلك .', 'Five: al-Mahabbah (love) of this word (Laa Ilaha Illa Allah) and what proves it and to be content with that.', 5),
(150, 1, 'الرابع : الصدق المنافي للكذب .', 'Four: as-Sidq (honesty) which negates falsehood, it prevents falling into hypocrisy.', 4),
(151, 1, 'الثالث : الإخلاص المنافي للكذب .', 'Three: al-Ikhlaas (sincerity) which negates Shirk (polytheism).', 3),
(152, 1, 'الثاني : اليقين ، وهو : كمال العلم بها ، المنافي للشك والريب .', 'Two: al-Yaqeen (certainty) which is the completeness of knowledge by it, it negates doubt and conjecture.', 2),
(153, 1, 'الأول : العلم بمعناها نفياً وإثباتاً', 'One: al-‘Ilm (knowledge) with the meaning of negation and affirmation.', 1),
(154, 4, 'تمت وصلى الله على محمد وآله وصحبه وسلم\r\n', 'This completes the treatise. May the peace and blessings of Allaah be on Muhammad, his family and Companions.', 28),
(155, 4, 'والدليل قوله تعالى \r\n(فَإِذَا رَكِبُوا فِي الْفُلْكِ دَعَوُا اللَّهَ مُخْلِصِينَ لَهُ الدِّينَ فَلَمَّا نَجَّاهُمْ إِلَى الْبَرِّ إِذَا هُمْ يُشْرِكُونَ) \r\n(العنكبوت:65)', 'The proof for this is Allaah’s statement: \r\n“And when they embark on a ship, they invoke Allaah making their Faith purely for Him alone. But when He brings them safely to land, behold they give a share of their worship to others.” \r\n[Surah Al-‘Ankaboot: 65]', 27),
(156, 4, 'الرابعة : أن مشركي زماننا أغلظ شركاً من الأولين لأن الأولين يشركون في الرخاء ويخلصون في الشدة ومشركو زماننا شركهم دائماً في الرخاء والشدة', 'The Fourth Rule: \r\nThe polytheists in our era are more severe in their (committing of) Shirk than the first polytheists (during the Prophet’s time). This was since the first polytheists used to ascribe partners to Allaah at times of ease and worship Him sincerely during times of hardship. However, the polytheists in our era constantly commit Shirk in times of ease as well as in times of hardship.', 26),
(157, 4, 'وحديث أبي واقد الليثي رضي الله عنه قال \r\n" خرجنا مع النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم إلي حنين ونحن حدثاء عهد بكفر وللمشركين سدرة يعكفون عندها وينوطون بها أسلحتهم يقال لها ذات أنواط فمررنا بسدرة فقلنا يا رسول الله اجعل لنا ذات أنواط كما لهم ذات أنواط الحديث "', 'And also the hadeeth of Abu Waaqid Al-Laythee (radyAllaahu ‘anhu) who said: \r\n“We went out with Allaah’s Messenger to (the Battle of) Hunayn, and we had just recently come out of Kufr (Disbelief). The polytheists used to have a lote-tree, which they would organize by and hang their swords on (seeking blessings from it); it was called Dhaat Anwaat. So we passed by a lote-tree and said: ‘O Messenger of Allaah! Make for us a Dhaat Anwaat, just as they have a Dhaat Anwaat?’”', 25),
(158, 4, 'ودليل الأشجار والأحجار قوله تعالى (أَفَرَأَيْتُمُ اللَّاتَ وَالْعُزَّى) \r\n(لنجم:19)  \r\n(وَمَنَاةَ الثَّالِثَةَ الْأُخْرَى) \r\n(لنجم:20)', 'The proof that they worshipped trees and stones is Allaah’s saying: \r\n“Have you then considered Al-Laat and Al-‘Uzzaa, and Manaat, the third other?” \r\n[Surah An-Najm: 19-20]', 24),
(159, 4, 'دليل الصالحين قوله تعالى \r\n(أُولَئِكَ الَّذِينَ يَدْعُونَ يَبْتَغُونَ إِلَى رَبِّهِمُ الْوَسِيلَةَ أَيُّهُمْ أَقْرَبُ وَيَرْجُونَ رَحْمَتَهُ وَيَخَافُونَ عَذَابَه) \r\n(الاسراء:  من الآية 57)', 'The proof that they worshipped the righteous people is Allaah’s saying: \r\n“Those whom they call unto (besides Allaah), they themselves seek the means of access to their Lord as to which of them will be the nearest (to Him). And they hope for His Mercy and fear His Torment.” \r\n[Surah Al-Israa: 57]', 23),
(160, 4, 'ودليل الأنبياء قوله تعالى \r\n( وَإِذْ قَالَ اللَّهُ يَا عِيسَى ابْنَ مَرْيَمَ أَأَنْتَ قُلْتَ لِلنَّاسِ اتَّخِذُونِي وَأُمِّيَ إِلَهَيْنِ مِنْ دُونِ اللَّهِ قَالَ سُبْحَانَكَ مَا يَكُونُ لِي أَنْ أَقُولَ مَا لَيْسَ لِي بِحَقٍّ إِنْ كُنْتُ قُلْتُهُ فَقَدْ عَلِمْتَهُ تَعْلَمُ مَا فِي نَفْسِي وَلا أَعْلَمُ مَا فِي نَفْسِكَ إِنَّكَ أَنْتَ عَلَّامُ الْغُيُوبِ ) (المائدة:116)', 'The proof that they worshipped the prophets is Allaah’s saying: \r\n“And when Allaah will say: ‘O ‘Eesaa, son of Maryam! Did you tell the people: Take me and my mother as gods besides Allaah?’ He will say: ‘Glory be to You, it is not for me to say what I have no right to say. Had I said such a thing, You would have surely known it. You know what is in my inner self yet I do not know what is in Your self. Verily, You re the All-Knower of the Unseen.’” \r\n[Surah Al-Maa’idah: 116]\r\n', 22),
(161, 4, 'ودليل الملائكة قوله تعالى \r\n(وَلا يَأْمُرَكُمْ أَنْ تَتَّخِذُوا الْمَلائِكَةَ وَالنَّبِيِّينَ أَرْبَاباً) \r\n(آل عمران: من الآية 80)', 'The proof that they worshipped the angels is Allaah’s saying: \r\n“And nor did he order you to take the angels and prophets as lords (besides Allaah).” \r\n[Surah Aali ‘Imraan: 80]', 21),
(162, 4, 'ودليل الشمس والقمر قوله تعالى \r\n( وَمِنْ آيَاتِهِ اللَّيْلُ وَالنَّهَارُ وَالشَّمْسُ وَالْقَمَرُ لا تَسْجُدُوا لِلشَّمْسِ وَلا لِلْقَمَرِ وَاسْجُدُوا لِلَّهِ الَّذِي خَلَقَهُنَّ إِنْ كُنْتُمْ إِيَّاهُ تَعْبُدُونَ) \r\n(فصلت:37)', 'The proof of them worshipping the sun and the moon is Allaah’s saying: \r\n“And among His signs are the night and the day and the sun and the moon. Do not prostrate to the sun or the moon, but rather prostrate to Allaah who created them, if it is truly He whom you worship.” \r\n[Surah Fussilat: 37]', 20),
(163, 4, 'والدليل قوله تعالى \r\n(وَقَاتِلُوهُمْ حَتَّى لا تَكُونَ فِتْنَةٌ وَيَكُونَ الدِّينُ كُلُّهُ لِلَّهِ ) \r\n(لأنفال: من الآية 39)', 'The proof for this is Allaah’s statement: \r\n“And fight against them until there is no more fitnah (trial, i.e. Shirk) and the Religion is all purely for Allaah alone.” \r\n[Surah Al-Anfaal: 39]', 19),
(164, 4, 'الثالثة : أن النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم ظهر على أناس متفرقين في عبادتهم منهم من يعبد الملائكة ومنهم من يعبد الأنبياء والصالحين ومنهم من يعبد الأشجار والأحجار ومنهم من يعبد الشمس والقمر وقاتلهم رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم ولم يفرق بينهم', 'The Third Rule:\r\nThe Prophet was sent to people that differed from one another in their worship. Among them were those who worshipped the angels. And among them were those who worshipped the prophets and righteous people. And among them were those who worshipped trees and stones. And among them were those who worshipped the sun and the moon. However, the Messenger of Allaah fought against (all of) them and did not differentiate between any of them.', 18),
(165, 4, 'كما قال تعالى \r\n(ِ مَنْ ذَا الَّذِي يَشْفَعُ عِنْدَهُ إِلَّا بِإِذْنِهِ) (البقرة: من الآية 255)', 'as Allaah says: \r\n“Who is it that will intercede in His presence except with His permission.” \r\n[Surah Al-Baqarah: 255]', 17),
(166, 4, 'والشفاعة المثبتة هي التي تطلب من الله والشافع مكرم بالشفاعة والمشفوع له من رضي الله قوله وعمله بعد الإذن', 'The Affirmed Intercession is that which is sought from Allaah. The intercessor is one who is granted the honor of being able to intercede (by Allaah), while the one who is interceded for is the one whom Allaah is pleased with his statements and actions. (All of these occur) after Allaah’s permission is granted,', 16),
(167, 4, 'والدليل قوله تعالى \r\n(يَا أَيُّهَا الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا أَنْفِقُوا مِمَّا رَزَقْنَاكُمْ مِنْ قَبْلِ أَنْ يَأْتِيَ يَوْمٌ لا بَيْعٌ فِيهِ وَلا خُلَّةٌ وَلا شَفَاعَةٌ وَالْكَافِرُونَ هُمُ الظَّالِمُونَ) \r\n(البقرة: 254)\r\n', 'The proof for this is Allaah’s saying: \r\n“O you who believe! Spend of that which We have provided for you, before a Day comes when there will be no bargaining nor friendship nor intercession. And it is the disbelievers who are the wrong-doers.” \r\n[Surah Al- Baqarah: 254]', 15),
(168, 4, 'فالشفاعة المنفية ما كانت تطلب من غير الله فيما لا يقدر عليه إلا الله\r\n', 'The Negated Intercession is that which is sought from someone other than Allaah in matters that no one has the ability to carry out except Allaah.', 14),
(169, 4, 'فدليل القربة قوله تعالى \r\n( وَالَّذِينَ اتَّخَذُوا مِنْ دُونِهِ أَوْلِيَاءَ مَا نَعْبُدُهُمْ إِلَّا لِيُقَرِّبُونَا إِلَى اللَّهِ زُلْفَى إِنَّ اللَّهَ يَحْكُمُ بَيْنَهُمْ فِي مَا هُمْ فِيهِ يَخْتَلِفُونَ إِنَّ اللَّهَ لا يَهْدِي مَنْ هُوَ كَاذِبٌ كَفَّارٌ )\r\n(الزمر: من الآية 3)\r\n', 'The proof for their seeking nearness (to Allaah) is His saying: \r\n“And those who take protectors besides Him (say): ‘We don’t worship them except to bring us closer to Allaah.’ Verily Allaah will judge between them concerning that which they differ in.  Verily, Allaah does not guide he who is a liar, a disbeliever.” \r\n[Surah Az-Zumar: 3]', 11);
INSERT INTO `pages` (`pageid`, `book_id`, `content_arabic`, `content_english`, `page_number`) VALUES
(170, 4, 'الشفاعة شفاعتان : شفاعة منفية وشفاعة مثبتة', 'Intercession is of two types: Intercession that is negated and Intercession that is affirmed.', 13),
(171, 4, 'ودليل الشفاعة قوله تعالى \r\n(وَيَعْبُدُونَ مِنْ دُونِ اللَّهِ مَا لا يَضُرُّهُمْ وَلا يَنْفَعُهُمْ وَيَقُولُونَ هَؤُلاءِ شُفَعَاؤُنَا عِنْدَ اللَّه)\r\n(يونس: من الآية 18)', 'The proof for their seeking intercession is Allaah’s saying: \r\n“And they worship besides Allaah things that harm them not nor benefit them. And they say: ‘These are our intercessors besides Allaah.’” \r\n[Surah Yoonus: 18]', 12),
(172, 4, 'الثانية : أنهم يقولون ما دعوناهم وتوجهنا إليهم إلا لطلب القربة والشفاعة', 'The Second Rule: They (i.e. the disbelievers) said: “We did not invoke them nor turn towards them except to seek nearness (to Allah) and (their) intercession.', 10),
(173, 4, 'والدليل قوله تعالى \r\n(قُلْ مَنْ يَرْزُقُكُمْ مِنَ السَّمَاءِ وَالْأَرْضِ أَمَّنْ يَمْلِكُ السَّمْعَ وَالْأَبْصَارَ وَمَنْ يُخْرِجُ الْحَيَّ مِنَ الْمَيِّتِ وَيُخْرِجُ الْمَيِّتَ مِنَ الْحَيِّ وَمَنْ يُدَبِّرُ الْأَمْرَ فَسَيَقُولُونَ اللَّهُ فَقُلْ أَفَلا تَتَّقُونَ) \r\n(يونس:31) .\r\n', 'The proof for this is Allaah’s saying: \r\n“Say: ‘Who provides for you from the sky and the earth, or who owns the hearing and the sight? And who brings out the living from the dead and brings out the dead from the living? And who administers the affairs?’ They will surely say: ‘Allaah.’ Say: ‘Will you then not be dutiful to Him?’” \r\n[Surah Yoonus: 31]', 9),
(174, 4, 'الأولى : أن تعلم أن الكفار الذين قاتلهم رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم مقرون بأن الله تعالى هو الخالق المدبر وأن ذلك لم يدخلهم في الإسلام', 'The First Rule: You must know that the disbelievers whom the Messenger of Allaah fought against agreed that Allaah was the Creator and the Administrator. But this (belief) did not cause them to enter into the fold of Islaam.', 8),
(175, 4, 'فإذا عرفت أن الشرك إذا خالط العبادة أفسدها وأحبط العمل وصار صاحبه من الخالدين في النار عرفت أن أهم ما عليك معرفة ذلك لعل الله أن يخلصك من هذه الشبكة وهي الشرك بالله الذي قال الله تعالى فيه…', 'So when you come to realize that Shirk – when mixed into one’s worship – spoils it, invalidates one’s actions, and makes the person who possesses it into one who will reside eternally in the Hellfire, you will know that the most important thing that is binding upon you is to gain knowledge of that, so that perhaps Allaah may absolve you from this trap, which is ascribing partners to Allaah (i.e. Shirk) about which Allaah said:...', 7),
(176, 4, 'فإذا عرفت أن الشرك إذا خالط العبادة أفسدها وأحبط العمل وصار صاحبه من الخالدين في النار عرفت أن أهم ما عليك معرفة ذلك لعل الله أن يخلصك من هذه الشبكة وهي الشرك بالله الذي قال الله تعالى فيه…\r\n\r\n', 'So when you come to realize that Shirk – when mixed into one’s worship – spoils it, invalidates one’s actions, and makes the person who possesses it into one who will reside eternally in the Hellfire, you will know that the most important thing that is binding upon you is to gain knowledge of that, so that perhaps Allaah may absolve you from this trap, which is ascribing partners to Allaah (i.e. Shirk) about which Allaah said:...', 6),
(177, 4, 'فإذا دخل الشرك في العبادة فسدت كالحدث إذا دخل في الطهارة', 'So if Shirk (mixing partners) enters into one’s worship, it ruins it, just like impurity when it enters into the (ritual) purity.', 5),
(178, 4, 'فإذا عرفت أن الله خلقك لعبادته فاعلم أن العبادة لا تسمى عبادة إلا مع التوحيد كما أن الصلاة لا تسمى صلاة إلا مع الطهارة\r\n', 'So when you come to realize that Allaah created you in order to worship Him, then know that worship is not called worship unless it is accompanied by Tawheed, just as prayer is not called that unless it is accompanied by (ritual) purity.', 4),
(179, 4, 'كما قال تعالى (وَمَا خَلَقْتُ الْجِنَّ وَالْأِنْسَ إِلَّا لِيَعْبُدُونِ)  (الذريات:56)', 'as Allaah says: “And I did not create the Jinn and mankind except to worship Me.”  \r\n[Surah Adh-Dhaariyaat: 56]', 3),
(180, 4, 'اعلم أرشدك الله لطاعته أن الحنيفية ملة إبراهيم أن تعبد الله وحده مخلصاً له الدين\r\n', 'Know, may Allaah grant you the ability to obey Him, that the Haneefiyyah, the religion of Ibraaheem is that you worship Allaah alone, making the Religion sincere for only Him.', 2),
(181, 4, 'أسأل الله الكريم رب العرش العظيم أن يتولاك في الدنيا والآخرة وأن يجعلك مباركاً أينما كنت وأن يجعلك ممن إذا أعطى شكر وإذا ابتلى صبر وإذا أذنب استغفر فإن هؤلاء الثلاث عنوان السعادة .', ' I ask Allaah, the Most Generous, Lord of the Great Throne to befriend you in this world and the Hereafter, and to make you blessed wherever you may be. And (I ask) that He make you from those who when they are given, are thankful; when they are tested, are patient; and when they sin, seek forgiveness (from Allaah). For indeed these three characteristics are the true signs of happiness.', 1),
(182, 1, 'متن شروط لا إله إلا الله', 'The Conditions of Laa Ilaha Illa Allah\r\n\r\nExtracted from "The Decreed Obligations that every Muslim man and woman must know".\r\n\r\nTaken from the works of the Reviver of the Twelfth Century: Shaykh-ul-Islaam Muhammad bin ‘Abdil-Wahhaab and from his grandchildren and others (May Allah Most High have mercy upon them all).\r\n\r\nCollected by the one in need of his All-Powerful Lord`s pardon His Eminence ash-Shaykh ‘Abdullah bin Ibraaheem bin ‘Uthmaan al-Qar`aawee (May Allah forgive him, his parents, his teachers, and all of the Muslims).', 0),
(183, 2, 'لامية لشيخ الإسلام ابن تيمية رحمه الله', 'This is a translation of the Laamiyyah poem which is ascribed to Shaykh al-Islaam Ibn Taymiyyah (rahimahullaah). \r\nIt is only 16 verses of poetry, easy to memorize, and a great starting point in memorization for a child or a beginner in knowledge. \r\nThis qaseedah has a written manuscript in Jaami''ah Malik Saud (no. 6/1928), being written in the year 1353H), and it is found alongside two other works, al-Wasiyyah al-Kubraa, and al-Adillah al-Bayyinah, both of which are known works of Ibn Taymiyyah. \r\nIt has been mentioned by the Scholar of Iraq, Nu''maan al-Alusi (rahimahullaah), in his excellent book "Jalaa'' al-Aynayn Fee Muhaakamah al-Ahmadayn." Shaykh Abd al-Salaam bin Burjis (rahimahullaah) included this qaseedah as being amongst the poetry of Ibn Taymiyyah in his work, "al-Saheeh min al-Nadhm al-Faseeh Li Shaykh al-Islaam Ibn Taymiyyah" and a number of Scholars have explanations of this qaseedah, from the contemporaries Shaykh Saalih al-Suhaymee and also Shaykh Ahmad al-Mardawi (d. 1236H) almost two hundred years ago. \r\nIts ascription to Ibn Taymiyyah is not decisively established, however, the contents of the poetry are in agreement with the creed of Ahl al-Sunnah, and due its brevity and shortness of length, it is worth attention.\r\n\r\nPoem Contents\r\n\r\nThe poem comprises major elements of the belief of the Salaf and touches upon\r\n\r\nThe excellence of the Companions,\r\nMaking tawassul to Allaah through one''s love of them,\r\nThe superiority of Abu Bakr al-Siddeeq (radiallaahu anhu),\r\nReferring back to the Qur''an and the Sunnah,\r\nBelieving in the verses of the attributes upon the way of the Salaf,\r\nRefuting the Ash''aris who base their view on the Qur''an from the saying of a Trinitarian Christian,\r\nBelief in seeing Allaah (the Ru''yah) in the Hereafter,\r\nBelief in Allaah''s descent to the lowest heaven without how,\r\nBelief in the Meezaan, Hawd and Siraat (from the affairs of the Hereafter),\r\nThe punishment of the Fire and the reward of Paradise in relation to Divine Wisdom its connection to the topic of al-qadar,\r\nThe questioning in the grave,\r\nAnd establishing this was the creed of the four Imaams.', 0),
(184, 3, 'متن الأصول الثلاثة للشيخ محمد بن عبد الوهاب رحمه الله', 'The Three Fundamental Principles is a brief booklet by Shaykh Muhammad ibn ‘Abdul-Wahhaab, rahimahullaah, who wrote this in order to convey to every Muslim that which is obligatory upon him to know – in fact the “three principles” are based on the three questions that we will all be asked in our graves.', 0),
(185, 4, 'متن القواعد الأربعة للشيخ محمد بن عبد الوهاب رحمه الله', 'Four Principles of Shirk is a brief booklet by Muhammad ibn Abdul Wahhab.\r\nThe author explains the dangerous concept of shirk through four simple principles. The sin of shirk - or associating partners with Allah - is the most reprehensible act that a person can do. It is for this reason that this sin is the one sin that Allah has promised He will never forgive. Unfortunately, many Muslims who are unaware of the reality of shirk fall into it out of ignorance. This short treatise is an ideal work for the Muslim in order to understand the essence of shirk, and thus essential reading for the one who wishes to avoid falling into the greatest trap of Shaytan. ', 0),
(186, 5, '', 'Then I will come to them from before them and behind them, from their right and from their left, and You will not find most of them as thankful ones (i.e. they will not be dutiful to You)." (Al-A''raf 7:17)\r\n\r\nAllah the Most High informs us how Iblees (may Allah curse him), has promised how he will strive to cause mankind to deviate from the Path of Allah - Islam. This is why no Muslim should remain complacent about being upon Eeman, but rather should continue to strive in worshipping Allah correctly till death. However, it is more obligatory that this worship be accompanied with the correct belief in Allah and correct actions as legislated by Him, the Most High. It is therefore imperative to study those beliefs and actions that oppose Islam and cause the one who adopts them to be eternally in the Hellfire (we ask Allah for protection from it).\r\n\r\nNawaaqid ul-Islam is another great book by Shaykh ul-Islam, Muhammad bin Abdul-Wahhaab, which clarifies what the Tawheed of the Prophets and Messengers actually was. However, this work explains it from the angle of those actions which nullify ones Tawheed. Though there are many things that nullify Tawheed, the author highlights 10 main ones. ', 0),
(187, 5, 'اعْلَمْ أَنَّ نَوَاقِضَ الْإِسْلاَمِ عَشَرَةٌ: \r\nالْأَوَّلُ : الشِّرْكُ فِي عِبَادَةِ اللهِ تَعَالَى ، قَالَ اللهُ تَعَالَى : { إِنَّ اللهَ لاَ يَغْفِرُ أَنْ يُشْرَكَ بِهِ وَيَغْفِرُ مَا دُونَ ذَلِكَ لِمَن يَشَاءُ } وَقَالَ : { إِنَّهُ مَن يُشْرِكْ بِاللهِ فَقَدْ حَرَّمَ اللهُ عَلَيْهِ الْجَنَّةَ وَمَأْوَاهُ النَّارُ وَمَا لِلظَّالِمِينَ مِنْ أَنْصَارٍ } وَمِنْهُ الذَّبْحُ لِغَيْرِ اللهِ ، كَمَنْ يَذْبَحُ لِلْجِنِّ أَوْ لِلْقَبْرِ .\r\n', 'Know that the Nullifiers of Islaam are ten.\r\nFirst: Shirk (associating partners) in the worship of Allah. Allah says:\r\n“Verily, Allah does not forgive that partners be associated with Him in\r\nworship (i.e. Shirk), but He forgives what is less than that to whom He\r\nwills.”\r\n[Surah An-Nisaa: 116]\r\nAnd He says:\r\n“Verily, the one who mixes partners in worship with Allah (Shirk), then\r\nParadise has been made forbidden for him and his final abode will be\r\nthe Hellfire. And the wrongdoers will not have any helpers (in Hell).”\r\n[Surah Al-Maa’idah: 72]\r\nWhat falls into this is performing sacrifices to someone other than Allah, such as\r\nthe person who offers a sacrifice to the Jinn or to a grave.', 1),
(188, 5, 'الثَّانِي : مَنْ جَعَلَ بَيْنَهُ وَبَيْنَ اللهِ وَسَائِطَ يَدْعُوهُمْ وَيَسْأَلُهُمُ الشَّفَاعَةَ وَيَتَوَكَّلُ عَلَيْهِمْ ، كَفَرَ إِجْمَاعاً . ', 'Second: Whoever places intermediaries between himself and Allah, calling unto\r\nthem and asking intercession from them, and seeking reliance in them, has\r\ncommitted disbelief according to the unanimous agreement (Ijmaa’).', 2),
(189, 5, 'الثَّالِثُ : مَنْ لَمْ يُكَفِّرِ الْمُشْرِكِينَ أَوْ شَكَّ فِي كُفْرِهِمْ أَوْ صَحَّحَ مَذْهَبَهُمْ كَفَر .', 'Third: Whoever does not hold the polytheists to be disbelievers, or has doubts\r\nabout their disbelief or considers their ways and beliefs to be correct, has\r\ncommitted disbelief.', 3),
(190, 5, 'الرَّابِعُ : مَنِ اعْتَقَدَ أَنَّ غَيْرَ هَدْيِ النَّبِيِّ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ أَكْمَلَ مِنْ هَدْيِهِ ، أَوْ أَنَّ حُكْمَ غَيْرِهِ أَحْسَنَ مِنْ حُكْمِهِ - كَالَّذِي يُفَضِّلُ حُكْمَ الطَّوَاغِيتِ عَلَى حُكْمِهِ - فَهُوَ كَافِرٌ . ', 'Fourth: Whoever believes that some guidance other than that of the Prophet’s\r\nﷺ is more complete than his guidance and that someone else’s judgement is\r\nbetter than his judgement, such as the one who prefers the judgement of the\r\nTawaagheet (pl. of Taaghoot; false deities/religions) over his judgement, then\r\nhe is a disbeliever.', 4),
(191, 5, 'الْخَامِسُ : مَنْ أَبْغَضَ شَيْئاً مِمَّا جَاءَ بِهِ الرَّسُولُ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ وَلَوْ عَمِلَ بِهِ ، كَفَرَ', 'Fifth: Whoever hates something that the Messenger came with, even though he\r\nmay act on it, has disbelieved.', 5),
(192, 5, 'السَّادِسُ : مَنِ اسْتَهْزَأَ بِشَيْءٍ مِنْ دِينِ الرَّسُولِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ أَوْ ثَوَابِهِ أَوْ عِقَابِهِ كَفَر، وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى : { وَلَئِنْ سَأَلْتَهُمْ لَيَقُولُنَّ إِنَّمَا كُنَّا نَخُوضُ وَنَلْعَبُ قُلْ أَبِاللهِ وَآيَاتِهِ وَرَسُولِهِ كُنْتُمْ تَسْتَهْزِءُونَ * لاَ تَعْتَذِرُوا قَدْ كَفَرَتُمْ بَعْدَ إِيمَانِكُمْ } . ', 'Sixth: Whoever mocks or ridicules any part of the Messenger’s Religion or its\r\nrewards or punishments has committed an act of disbelief. The proof for this is\r\nAllah’s statement:\r\n“Say: ‘Was it Allah and His verses and His Messenger that you were\r\nmocking? Make no excuses, you have disbelieved after having had\r\nfaith.”\r\n[Surah At-Tawbah: 65-66]', 6),
(193, 5, 'الثَّامِنُ : مُظَاهَرَة ُالْمُشْرِكِينَ وَمُعَاوَنَتُهُمْ عَلَى الْمُسْلِمِينَ ، وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى : { وَمَنْ يَتَوَلَّهُمْ مِنْكُمْ فَإِنَّهُ مِنْهُمْ إِنَّ اللهَ لاَ يَهْدِي الْقَوْمَ الظَّالِمِينَ }\r\n', 'Eighth: Supporting and assisting the polytheists against the Muslims. The proof\r\nfor this is Allah’s statement\r\n“And whoever amongst you takes them (i.e. the disbelievers) as allies\r\nand protectors then he is indeed from among them. Verily, Allah does\r\nnot guide a wrong-doing people.”\r\n[Surah Al-Maa’idah: 51]', 8),
(194, 5, 'السَّابِعُ : السِّحْرُ ، وَمِنْهُ الصَّرْفُ وَالْعَطْفُ ، فَمَنْ فَعَلَهُ أَوْ رَضِيَ بِهِ كَفَرَ ، وَالدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى :{  وَمَا يُعَلِّمَانِ مِنْ أَحَدٍ حَتَّىٰ يَقُولَا إِنَّمَا نَحْنُ فِتْنَةٌ فَلَا تَكْفُرْ } . ', 'Seventh: Sorcery, which includes magic spells that cause a person to hate\r\nsomething he seeks after (sarf) or love something he doesn’t seek after (‘atf). So\r\nwhoever performs it or is pleased with it being done, has committed disbelief.\r\nThe proof for this is Allah’s statement:\r\n“And neither of these two (angels) would teach anyone until they had\r\nfirst said to them: ‘We are only a trial (for the people), so do not\r\ncommit disbelief.’”\r\n[Surah Al- Baqarah: 102]', 7),
(195, 5, 'التَّاسِعُ : مَنِ اعْتَقَدَ أَنَّ بَعْضَ النَّاسِ يَسَعُهُ الْخُرُوجَ عَنْ شَرِيعَةِ مُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ، كَمَا وَسِعَ الْخَضِرُ الْخُرُوجَ عَنْ شَرِيعَةِ مُوسَى عَلَيْهِ السَّلاَم ، فَهُوَ كَافِرٌ . ', 'Ninth: Whoever believes that it is permitted for some people to be free of\r\n(implementing) the Sharee’ah (revealed laws) of Muhammad ﷺ (i.e. Islaam),\r\njust as it was permitted for Al-Khidr to be free from the Sharee’ah of Moosaa,\r\nthen he is a disbeliever', 9),
(196, 5, 'الْعَاشِرُ : الْإِعْرَاضُ عَنْ دِينِ اللهِ تَعَالَى ، لاَ يَتَعَلَّمُهُ وَلاَ يَعْمَلُ بِهِ، وَ الدَّلِيلُ قَوْلُهُ تَعَالَى : { وَمَنْ أَظْلَمُ مِمَّنْ ذُكِّرَ بِآيَتِ رَبِّهِ ثُمَّ أَعْرَضَ عَنْهَا إِنَّا مِنَ الْمُجْرِمِينَ مُنْتَقِمُونَ }', 'Tenth: Turning away from Allah’s Religion, not learning it or implementing it\r\n(is an act of disbelief). The proof for this is Allah’s saying:\r\n“And who does more wrong than he who is reminded of the ayaat\r\n(signs/verses) of his Lord, then turns away from them. Verily, We shall\r\nextract retribution from the criminals.”\r\n[Surah As-Sajdah: 22]', 10),
(197, 5, 'وَلاَ فَرْقَ فِي جَمِيعِ هَذِهِ بَيْنَ الْهَازِلِ وَالْجَادِّ وَالْخَائِفِ إِلاَّ الْمُكْرَهِ، وَكُلُّهَا مِنْ أَعْظَمِ مَا يَكُونُ خَطَراً وَ أَكْثَرُ مَا يَكُونُ وُقُوعاً، فَيَنْبَغِي لِلْمُسْلِمِ أَنْ يَحْذَرَهَا وَيَخَافَ مِنْهَا عَلَى نَفْسِهِ، نَعُوذُ بِاللهِ مِنْ مُوجِبَاتِ غَضَبِهِ وَأَلِيمِ عِقَابِهِ. ', 'There is no difference, with regard to (committing any of) these nullifiers,\r\nbetween the one who jokes, the one who is serious or the one who does so out\r\nof fear. However, the one who commits them due to being coerced (is\r\nexcused). All of these (ten) matters are from the gravest in danger and from\r\nthose that most often occur. So the Muslim must beware of them and fear from\r\nthese acts befalling him. We seek refuge in Allah from those things that bring about His Anger and painful Punishment. May the peace and blessing be on the\r\nbest of His creatures, Muhammad ﷺ', 11);
INSERT INTO `reciters` (`reciter_id`, `reciter_name_arabic`, `reciter_name_english`) VALUES
(1, 'أبو أحمد الشيظمي', 'Abu Ahmed Ash-Shaythamee'),
(2, '', 'Laamiya no audio yet'),
(4, '', 'Unknown'),
(3, 'محمد سعيد رسلان', 'Mohammed Sa''eed Raslan');
INSERT INTO `sharh` (`sharh_id`, `page_id`, `content`) VALUES
('1', '115', 'This is a supplication from Shaikhul-Islaam for the questioner that Allah grants him guidance. For\r\nthe one who asks the likes of this question, is one of two men:\r\n1. Either he is a questioner who wants to know the Aqeedah of the one questioned so he can\r\ntreat him accordingly\r\n2. Or either he is a beginner who is respecting the one questioned and venerating him due to\r\nwhat he sees [from him] of the signs of guidance. This is the most common case with\r\nregards to this question. And Allah is the one who facilitates.\r\n'),
('1', '114', 'The Shaikh informed [the reader] here that his Aqeedah has come after research and returning to evidences. \r\nSo like this he is firm. \r\nHe will not turn away from it whatever may be the cause for turning away and not change it whatever the temptations may be.\r\n'),
('1', '113', 'He (may Allah have mercy upon him) indicates [here] that from his mathhab is the love for all the\r\nCompanions (may Allah be pleased with them) without an exception. Due to Allah’s statement after\r\nmentioning the Muhaajireen and Ansaar in surah Hashr:\r\nِن\r\nا بِا َلإيَمـ\r\nِذيَن َسَبقُونَ\r\nا الَّ\r\nا َو ِلإ ْخَوِننَ\r\nنَ\r\nْغِفْر لَ\r\nا ا\r\nِذيَن َجآُءوا ِمن َبْعِدِهْم َيقُولُو َن َرَّبنَ\r\nَوالَّ\r\nAnd those who came after them say: "Our Lord! Forgive us and our brethren who have preceded us\r\nin Faith [59:10]\r\nAnd due to His statement:\r\nُهْم\r\nِر ُر َحَمآُء َبْينَ\r\nا\r\nِشَّدآ ُء َعلَى الُْكفَّ\r\nَ\r\nِذيَن َمَعُه أ\r\nِ َوالَّ\r\nُّم َحَّمٌد َّر ُسوُل االلهَّ\r\nMuhammad is the Messenger of Allah, and those who are with him are severe against disbelievers,\r\nand merciful among themselves. [48:29]\r\nAnd His statement:\r\nْح َت ال َّشَجَرِة\r\nُعونَ َك تَ\r\nِ\r\nُيَباي\r\nِذْ\r\nُم ْؤِمِنيَن إ\r\nَعِن الْ\r\nْد َر ِض َي االلهَُّ\r\nقَ\r\nلَّ\r\nIndeed, Allah was pleased with the believers when they gave their Bai''a (pledge) to you (O\r\nMuhammad) under the tree [48:18]\r\nAnd His statement:\r\nَعَّد\r\nَ\r\nَعنْ ُه َوأ\r\nُهْم َوَر ُضواْ\r\nَعنْ\r\nٍن َّر ِض َى االلهَُّ\r\nِ ْح َسا\r\nَبُعو ُهم بِإ\r\nِذيَن اتَّ\r\nِر َوالَّ\r\nَصـ\r\nنْ\r\nِجِريَن َوالأَ\r\nُمَهـ\r\nَّولُو َن ِم َن الْ\r\nٌّ\r\nَوال َّسـبِقُو َن الا\r\nَعِظيُم\r\nْوُز الْ\r\nفَ\r\nِل َك الْ\r\nَبداً ذَ\r\nَ\r\nَهـُر َخـِلِديَن ِفيَهآ أ\r\nنْ\r\nَها الأَ\r\nْحتَ\r\nْجِري تَ\r\nـ ٍت تَ\r\nُهْم َجنَّ\r\nلَ\r\n10\r\nAnd the first to embrace Islam of the Muhajirun (those who migrated from Makkah to Al-Madinah)\r\nand the Ansar (the citizens of Al-Madinah who helped and gave aid to the Muhajirun) and also those\r\nwho followed them exactly (in Faith). Allah is well-pleased with them as they are well-pleased with\r\nHim. He has prepared for them Gardens under which rivers flow (Paradise), to dwell therein\r\nforever. That is the supreme success [9:100]\r\nAnd His statement:\r\nلُو ُب\r\nُع ْسَرِة ِمن َبْعِد َما َكاَد َيِزيُغ قُ\r\nَبُعوُه ِفى َسا َعِة الْ\r\nِذيَن اتَّ\r\nِر الَّ\r\nن َصـ\r\nٌّ\r\nِجِريَن َوالا\r\nُمَهـ\r\nبِ ِّى َوالْ\r\nا َب االله َعلَى النَّ\r\nْد تَ\r\nقَ\r\nلَ\r\nْر ُض بِ َما\r\nِهُم الأَ\r\nْي\r\nْت َعلَ\r\nَ\r\nَضاق\r\nا\r\nِذَ\r\nَحتَّى إ\r\nفُواْ\r\nِذيَن ُخلِّ\r\nِة الَّ\r\nَ\r\nـث\r\nلَ\r\nَّ\r\nنَّ ُه بِ ِهْم َر ُءو ٌف َّر ِحيٌم َو َعلَى الث\r\nِ\r\nِهْم إ\r\nْي\r\nا َب َعلَ\r\nَّم تَ\r\nُهْم ثُ\r\nٍق ِّمنْ\r\nِري\r\nَ\r\nف\r\nَّوا ُب\r\nُهَو التَّ\r\nَّن االلهََّ\r\nِ\r\nإ\r\nِهْم ِلَيُتوُبواْ\r\nْي\r\nا َب َعلَ\r\nَّم تَ\r\nْيِه ثُ\r\nلَ\r\nِ\r\nَّلا إ\r\nِ\r\nِ إ\r\nِم َن االلهَّ\r\nَ\r\nَجأ\r\nن َّلا َملْ\r\nَ\r\nأ\r\nنُّواْ\r\nُسُهْم َوظَ\r\nنفُ\r\nَ\r\nِهْم أ\r\nْي\r\nْت َعلَ\r\nَ\r\nَر ُحَب ْت َو َضاق\r\nَم َع ال َّصـِدِقيَن\r\nَوُكونُواْ\r\nااللهََّ\r\nقُواْ\r\nاتَّ\r\nِذيَن َءاَمنُواْ\r\nُّيَها الَّ\r\nَ\r\nالَّر ِحيُم ­ َيـأ\r\nAllah has forgiven the Prophet, the Muhajirun (Muslim emigrants who left their homes and came to\r\nAl-Madinah) and the Ansar (Muslims of Al-Madinah) who followed him (Muhammad) in the time of\r\ndistress (Tabuk expedition, etc.), after the hearts of a party of them had nearly deviated (from the\r\nRight Path), but He accepted their repentance. Certainly, He is unto them full of Kindness, Most\r\nMerciful.\r\nAnd (He did forgive also) the three [who did not join the Tabuk expedition (whom the Prophet left\r\n(i.e. he did not give his judgement in their case, and their case was suspended for Allah''s Decision)\r\ntill for them the earth, vast as it is, was straitened and their ownselves were straitened to them, and\r\nthey perceived that there is no fleeing from Allah, and no refuge but with Him. Then, He accepted\r\ntheir repentance, that they might repent (unto Him). Verily, Allah is the One Who accepts\r\nrepentance, Most Merciful. [9:117-118]\r\nThese verses and other than it are evidences for the obligation to love the Companions (may Allah\r\nbe pleased with them). [They are] those who were afflicted alongside the Prophet (صلى الله عليه وسلم (with a fair\r\ntrial, which was a cause for Allah’s pleasure with them and their firmness in aiding their Prophet\r\n(صلى الله عليه وسلم (upon the Truth.\r\nLike this, it is obligatory upon every Muslim to love all the Companions and not speak bad about\r\nanyone of them due to his statement (صلى الله عليه وسلم:(\r\nِرُكو ِلي َصا ِحبِي\r\nا\r\nنُْتْم تَ\r\nَ\r\nَه ْل أ\r\n11\r\nWon''t you then give up harming my Companion?\r\n[Bukhari no. 3361]\r\nAnd:\r\nُه\r\nِصيفَ\r\nَحِدِهْم َو َلا نَ\r\nَ\r\nْدَر َك ُمَّد أ\r\nَ\r\nَهًبا َما أ\r\nُحٍد ذَ\r\nُ\r\nَق ِمثْ َل أ\r\nفَ\r\nنْ\r\nَ\r\nَحَدُكْم أ\r\nَ\r\nَّن أ\r\nَ\r\nْو أ\r\nِسي بَِيِدِه لَ\r\nفْ\r\nِذي نَ\r\nَوالَّ\r\nَ\r\nْصَحابِي ف\r\nَ\r\nُسُّبوا أ\r\nَلا تَ\r\nDo not revile my Companions, for by The One in Whose Hand is my soul! If any one of you were\r\nto spend the equivalent of Mount Uhud in gold, it would not equal a Mudd (handful) spent by\r\nanyone of them, nor even half a Mudd." [Muslim no. 2540 and others]\r\nAnd his (Shaykhul Islam ibn Taymiyyah’s) statement:\r\nAnd through the love of the household of the Prophet​ ​(صلى الله عليه وسلم​ ​(do I seek a\r\nmeans to Allah\r\nThat is: through the love of the household of the Prophet (صلى الله عليه وسلم (do I seek a means to Allah. I hope\r\nthat my sins will be forgiven and that I enter the entrance on the Day of Judgement of those who\r\nare pleased with the Companions and the Prophet’s household. Allah says:\r\nْرَبى\r\nقُ\r\nِفى الْ\r\nَمَوَّدةَ\r\nَّلا الْ\r\nِ\r\nإ\r\nْجراً\r\nَ\r\nْيِه أ\r\nَلُُكْم َعلَ\r\nْسـ\r\nَ\r\nل َّلا أ\r\nقُ\r\nNo reward do I ask of you for this except to be kind to me for my kinship with you. [42:23]\r\nThat is: except that you love my kinship, respect them, and venerate them due to their nearness to\r\nme and my companionship.\r\nIt comes in the Hadith from the Prophet (صلى الله عليه وسلم: (\r\nٍ\r\nَرْي ٍش َبِني َها ِشم\r\nفَى ِم ْن قُ\r\nَوا ْصطَ\r\nةَ\r\nانَ\r\nَرْي ًشا ِم ْن ِكنَ\r\nفَى قُ\r\nِ ْسَما ِعيَل َوا ْصطَ\r\nِد إ\r\nِم ْن َولَ\r\nةَ\r\nانَ\r\nفَى ِكنَ\r\nا ْصطَ\r\nَّن االلهََّ\r\nِ\r\nإ\r\n\r\nِش\r\nاِني ِم ْن َبِني َها\r\nفَ\r\nَوا ْصطَ\r\nVerily Allah granted eminence to Kinana from amongst the descendants of Isma''il, and he granted\r\neminence to the Quraish amongst Kinana, and he granted eminence to Banu Hashim amongst the\r\nQuraish, and he granted me eminence from the tribe of Banu Hashim. [Saheeh Muslim no. 2276]\r\n');
INSERT INTO `shurooh` (`id`, `title_english`, `title_arabic`, `author`, `language`, `book_id`, `translated_by`, `published_by`) VALUES
(1, 'Sufficiency For the Questioner in Regards to What is in the Laamiyyah of Shaikhul-Islaam of [Aqeedah] Issues', 'غنية السائل بما في لامية شيخ الإسلام من مسائل', '3', '1', 2, 'Faisal Ibn Abdul Qaadir Ibn Hassan\r\nAbu Sulaymaan\r\n', ' Darul-Minhaaj print 1436 First Edition'),
(2, 'Explanation of The Nullifiers of Islaam\r\nOf the Imaam and Mujaddid - Muhammad bin ‘Abdil-Wahhaab -', NULL, '4', '1', 5, 'abu maryam isma’eel alarcon', NULL);
